title: cole slaw
directions: Shred
the
cabbage
first with a grater and chop fine. Shred the
carrots
and chop fine.
Mix the cabbage, the carrots,
the vinegar,
the
sugar,
the salt and mix.
Core the apple last and add
to
the cabbage mixture.
Finally, add the salad dressing and mix
well.
Add
the
milk gradually and be careful not to make the
slaw
too
watery.
Serves
to 12 people.
With spaghetti, chitterlings, just about anything you like to eat.
This slaw can be served with it.

title: shoestring salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine tuna, onion, carrots and celery.
In a separate bowl, mix salad dressing with milk or cream.
Pour dressing over tuna/vegetable mixture; mix well.
Just before serving, mix shoestring potatoes with prepared salad.

title: yam casserole
directions: Mash the yams until smooth.
Season with nutmeg, cinnamon, pecans or walnuts, brown sugar and crushed pineapple.
Blend together and put in casserole dish; bake 25 minutes at 350°.
I like to sprinkle shredded coconut over the mixture before baking.

title: spicy ham sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Good with baked ham, smoked pork cuts and ducks.

title: savory onion chicken(for microwave)
directions: Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat with dry soup mix. Arrange in baking dish, skin side up and thick meaty pieces to the outside edges of dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 18 to 22 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk together well.
Place layer of graham crackers in bottom of dish.
Place a layer of pudding on top of crackers, then another layer of graham crackers, then pudding and end with a layer of crackers on top.
Top with a can of chocolate frosting (place in microwave for 30 seconds for easier spreading). Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: butter tarts
directions: Cut rolled pie crust with 3-inch cutter.
Place in muffin or tart pan.
Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Fill each crust 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: gluhwein
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add red wine.
Heat to nearly boiling and add 2 tablespoons of rum to each cup.
Serve.
(Great on a cold winter night; do not drive.)

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spray bottom of glass rectangular pan with Pam.
Line bottom first with the chipped beef.
Wrap the individual pieces of chicken with a slice of bacon (uncooked of course).
Place chicken on top of chipped beef.
Mix together the cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in conventional home oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
(Absolutely mouth watering!)

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Boil noodles as directed.
Add browned beef to Ragu and season to taste with onion salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (spray with cooking spray).

Layer noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 Ragu mix and 1/2 sliced Mozzarella cheese. Save a little Ragu mix for top of layers after repeating layers. Top with all the shredded Mozzarella and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Broil cheese on top if desired.

title: chicken pasta salad oriental
directions: Prepare pasta salad pasta and vegetable envelope using package directions.
Combine pasta salad seasoning mix, lemon rind, lemon juice, oil and honey in small bowl; mix well.
Combine pasta and vegetable mixture, seasoning mixture, water chestnuts, carrots, green onions, cashews and pasta salad Parmesan cheese in bowl; mix well.
Fold in chicken.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut grapes in half.
Cut up bananas, walnuts, apple (with skin on) and celery.
Stir Miracle Whip, sugar and milk until smooth and creamy.
Add to fruit; chill and serve.

title: cake box cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead as you would for bread. Divide dough into half.
Roll out each into a rectangle (about 1/2 inch thick).
Spread each with melted butter and brown sugar. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up each rectangle and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water; set aside.
Melt margarine. Cream with sugar in a large bowl.
Add beaten eggs.
Add dissolved yeast to mixture.
Add flour; stir until well mixed.
Place in an airtight container (will keep for 2 weeks).

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, margarine, milk and coconut.
Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix garlic (chopped) in hamburger.
Add salt and pepper; brown mixture.
After browning, add rest of ingredients; cook until cheese melts.
Boil fine spaghetti and top with sauce.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cover and let marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 12-inch cooking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped up potato chips and place on top.
Heavenly!

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed, except cheese. Pour half the batter into a greased, 9 x 12-inch baking dish and sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Add remaining batter and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: half-time spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine in a large bowl sugar, margarine, salt and scalded milk.
Cool by adding cold water. Blend in the egg and yeast, then the flour and blend well.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in volume, 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir down and spoon into well-greased muffin tins, filling about half full.
Let rise until dough reaches to edge of muffin cup and is rounded in center, about 45 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, margarine, almonds and powdered sugar in a medium bowl with fork until crumbly.
Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar and the eggs.
Stir in 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Pour cream cheese mixture over hot crust.
Bake just until center is set, about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: sausage hors d'oeuvres
directions: Make little balls; put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 400° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be frozen, baked or unbaked.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and mix with other.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Makes 2 big loaves or 4 small ones.

title: fried rice with seafood
directions: Cook rice; allow it to cool.
Heat a wok or a large frying pan; add the oil.
Saute the garlic and yellow onion until the onion is clear.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir-fry until hot.
This is a simple dish to fix but is delicious.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in citric acid and hot water. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Yield: 2 gallons.

title: rice porcupines
directions: Mix together ground beef, uncooked rice, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Form into small balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Place in a covered baking dish.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over apricots in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 450°.
Take out and crumble Ritz crackers over.
Put back in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baker's dough
directions: Should be the consistency of play dough. Play and create!

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereals into large bowl.
In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated. Sift 1/2 the powdered sugar into large zipper bag.
Add 1/2 the cereal mixture. Seal and shake until all pieces are well coated. Spread on a jelly roll pan to cool.
Repeat.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Whip butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and beat well. Add biscuit mix and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add potato flakes and stir only to mix well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package.
Drain and set aside. Combine ground beef, green peppers and onion in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and vent one side for steam.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring at 2 minute intervals.
Drain.
Add noodles, pizza sauce, water, garlic salt, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 17 to 19 minutes, stirring at 6 minute intervals.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: spicy venison jerky
directions: Slice meat 1/8-inch thick along its grain.
Mix marinade ingredients in bowl.
Brush on meat anytime and as many times to taste.
(I usually make 8 times the recipe for a huge batch and marinate the meat overnight with 1/4 sauce.)
Put meat on broiler pan in 200° oven for 5 to 6 hours.

title: black walnut taffy
directions: Boil sugar, water, syrup and vinegar until it makes a hard ball in water (hard enough when put in water it will break like glass).
Add butter and walnuts.
Cool and pull.
Break into small pieces.

title: two tone fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla and stir until mixture is smooth.
To 2 cups of hot mixture, add the butterscotch morsels and 1/2 cup of walnuts.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour evenly into greased 9-inch square pan.
To remaining hot mixture, add chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup nuts.
Stir until morsels are melted and smooth.
Pour over butterscotch mixture and chill until firm.
Yields 2 1/2 pounds.

title: applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a sauce pan and cook until tender. Mash with a potato masher or an electric mixer until smooth. Put apple sauce in air tight container and place in refrigerator to cool. Top with cinnamon and enjoy.

title: corn and beef casserole
directions: On medium heat, brown the beef, chopped onion, celery and green pepper in heavy skillet.

title: wild turkey in the straw
directions: Shake turkey pieces in a mixture of flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag to coat evenly.
Brown turkey pieces in hot oil in a large skillet. Remove and reserve.

Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the pan drippings. Saute onion and garlic until soft; stir in chicken broth and lemon juice until well blended. Return turkey to skillet. Baste with part of the sauce.
Cover skillet. Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes or until turkey is tender when pierced with a two-tined fork.
Line a heated serving platter with "Straw" and arrange turkey pieces on top. Arrange lemon slices and ripe olives on turkey. Cover with foil and keep hot while preparing sauce.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Chop onions, celery and peppers.
Saute butter, onions, celery, peppers and flour.
Add crawfish tails.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add half and half, Velveeta cheese, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes.
Cook fettucini.
Mix everything together.
Spread into pan; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish the pork chops, onion, potatoes and bell pepper. Cover with cream of mushroom soup and a little water. Bake at 325° to 350° approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: diabetic chocolate pudding(calories: 185)
directions: Soak the gelatin in one tablespoon water.
Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add milk gradually to beaten egg and return to boiler.
Cook until the mixture coats a spoon and then add melted chocolate.
Remove from fire and add gelatin.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add noncaloric sweetener and vanilla.
Beat and pour into mold and chill.
If the mixture curdles, beat well with an eggbeater.

title: parsleyed potato and egg salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets in lightly salted water to cover. Cook about 30 minutes or until just barely tender.
Cool and peel if desired.
Cut into large chunks.
Cut eggs into quarters or chop coarsely.
Place in center of potatoes.
Cover with parsley.
Beat dressing ingredients until creamy.
Drizzle over salad, tossing gently but thoroughly.
Serve at room temperature.
Good served with cold chicken, turkey or pork, herbed Melba toast and iced tea.

title: purple hull pea jelly
directions: Rinse pea hulls. Fill a large Dutch oven (do not use cast iron) with hulls and enough water to make hulls float. Bring to a boil; boil for 45 minutes. Strain juice. Bring 4 c. juice to a boil. Add Sure Jell; bring to a boil again. Add sugar and stir until it returns to a boil; cook 15 minutes. Remove from heat; skim top. Pour into sterile jars and seal. Makes about 3 1/2 pints.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until edges start to brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat butter and soup; stir in sour cream, onion and cheese. Add potatoes and toss.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Grease a 6 x 10-inch casserole and fill.
Toss 1/4 cup corn flakes with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6. Double recipe for 10 to 12.

title: texas taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Fritos, as early as an hour ahead.
Add Fritos to mixture just before serving.

title: spinach and mushroom crepes
directions: Prepare crepes (recipe follows)

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on toasted or plain bread.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll in white sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Toss into Bundt pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar.
Pour over quartered biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Take out of pan immediately so it won't stick.

title: raisin mumbles
directions: Mix butter with sugar, add dry ingredients, then oats. Press half of mixture into greased 8 or 9 inch pan. Top with filling.

title: new german chocolate cake
directions: Mix up cake mix, then mix powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Grease pan.
Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Pour in cake mix, then dip the other mix into cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Flip over out on cake plate to cool.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes in large, mixing bowl with 1/2 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Add onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 3 quart buttered casserole.
Combine cornflakes and butter.
Cover top of potato mixture with these. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glop
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, pour large, ice-filled glasses 2/3 full of fruit juice mixture.
Fill with 7-Up and stir.

title: burritos
directions: Cook hamburger meat until well done.
Mix chili and beans into hamburger meat.
Cook over low heat.
Put hamburger meat mixture into tortilla shells and wrap.
Put into baking dish; cover with more hamburger mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is well melted.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions (or chop); brown in butter.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Arrange toast pieces on top of soup (optional).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and water into a large mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips and 1/2 of the shaved German chocolate.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix remaining shaved chocolate and confectioners sugar together.
Cool cake 10 minutes and dust with confectioners sugar mix.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts.
Blend until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup and press remaining mixture into 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper and brown meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, mushroom soup, and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.
Cut cheese and add to hot noodles.
Stir until melted.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, mix first 6 ingredients. Marinate for 1 day, then place pork chops on grill over hot charcoals.
Cook until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill, covered 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables. Makes 3 cups.

title: beans supreme
directions: Brown onion and ground chuck or chicken; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: In a plastic bag combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time, shake to coat.
In skillet brown chicken in the shortening.
Transfer to a 3-quart casserole.
In same skillet cook celery and onion until tender but not brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in soup, water and pimiento.
Pour over chicken. Cover.
Bake at 350° until tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with rice. Serves 4 to 5.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In large casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes (season), then diced cheese. Repeat until full. Pour canned milk gently over mixture. Bake about 30 minutes at 350° (until cheese and milk have created a cheese sauce).

title: divine yogurt pineapple rings
directions: Put pineapple rings on a plate.
Put strawberry yogurt in middle of pineapple ring.
Put sprinkles on top of yogurt.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat together margarine, 1 1/2 c. sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add flour and baking powder.
Blend well.
Add one large glass of sour cream and baking soda.
Set aside. For the topping, mix 1/2 c. sugar, cinnamon and chocolate chips.
Spread 1/2 of the cake batter in greased 13 X 9 X 2 pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the topping on. Layer on
remaining cake batter and end with remainder of the topping.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: dixie pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar and flour which have been mixed together.
Add melted margarine and mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix preceeding ingredients and pour over fresh mushrooms. Allow to soak for several hours.

title: festive cranberry torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Mix and press onto bottom and sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine cranberries and 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add unbeaten egg whites, orange juice, vanilla and salt.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer until frothy, then beat at high speed 6 to 8 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
In small bowl, whip cream to soft peaks. Fold into cranberry mixture.
Turn into crust.
Freeze firm.
To serve, remove torte to serving platter.
Spoon Glaze over top. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Make crust and Glaze first.
Can be made ahead and stored in freezer.

title: amish barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix mushroom soup with catsup, Worcestershire sauce and chopped onion.
Pour over pork chops and bake 2 hours at 375°. Cook in heavy saucepan sprayed with Pam.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix next 4 ingredients and add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter.
Coat carrots with the sauce.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots crosswise and boil until tender; cool and drain. Mix sugar, tomato soup, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire and mustard. Bring to boil.
Chop onion, bell pepper and celery and mix with carrots.
Pour hot sauce over mixture and marinate for several days in refrigerator before serving.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Combine first three ingredients, and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add soup, and stir until melted. Makes 10 -1 c. servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk; pour over bread.
Add vanilla, sugar, salt, butter and slightly beaten eggs; mix well.
Add raisins.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven in pan of water for at least 1 hour, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tac0 soup
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 1 hour and then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: date log
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and pecans, mixing well.
Shape into two 11-inch logs and roll each in coconut. Cool; slice thin.

title: oven barbecued brisket
directions: Cook onion in oil until transparent.
Add rest of ingredients except meat.
Simmer half an hour.
Pour over meat.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Let sit half an hour before slicing.

title: celery almondine
directions: Cook celery and onion in salted, boiling water until just barely done.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Saute almonds in butter, sprinkle over mixture.

Top with shredded cheese and buttered bread crumbs which have been lightly tossed together. Bake in preheated 375° oven until hot and bubbly, about 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8. (This may be prepared early in day and baked just before serving.)

title: crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with onion, garlic, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise. Place in flat pan and chill overnight. Next day, spread bottle of cocktail sauce over cream cheese; top with chilled crabmeat. Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
When cool, cut in half and grate the yolks. Mix yolks with mayonnaise, sour cream and the prepared mustard.
Fill the egg whites with the above ingredients.
Makes 24 halves.

title: amish bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve 1 package dry yeast in half cup warm water.
Stir in 2 cups warm water, 2 cups flour and 1 tablespoon sugar or honey.
Beat until smooth.
Cover bowl with cheesecloth. Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 days or until mixture has a fermented aroma, stirring 2 to 3 times a day.
Fermentation time depends on room temperature; a warmer room makes it ferment faster.
After this, store in a jar covered with cheesecloth and refrigerate.
Do not cover jar with a lid.

title: janet cruz's hot potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes; cook in boiling water 30 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; save 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.

Saute onions, green onion and celery in reserved bacon drippings until tender; set aside. Combine flour, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard in medium saucepan; add vinegar and water and cook ten minutes over medium heat or until slightly thickened.
Combine potatoes and onion mixture in a large mixing bowl; top with vinegar mixture, tossing gently. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Dredge finely cut dates, candy, coconut and nuts in 1 cup sifted flour.
(Use kitchen scissors dipped in hot water for cutting orange slices and dates.)

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix crackers with melted butter.
Put half of crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix cheese, Veg-All and mayonnaise. Pour over crackers.
Top with remaining buttered crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable-cheese spread
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Mix in seasoned salt and garlic powder. Fold in carrot, zucchini, celery, green onion, green pepper and pimento.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add onions, cheeses and bacon.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crush Doritos.
Grate cheese.
Brown ground meat; season with onion.
Drain off grease.
Heat together the soup, enchilada sauce, taco sauce and Milnot.
Do not boil.
Layer in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan the meat, then Doritos, then sauce, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: You will need 12 toothpicks (wooden).

title: baked beets
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim and wash beets, but do not peel. Place beets in an ovenproof pan and add about 1/4-inch of water. Cover and cook for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check water level occasionally and add if necessary. When ready to serve, cut an "X" into the top of each beet and squeeze sides of beet together to open the "X."
Place 1 teaspoon of butter on top and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and soda.
Add the sifted ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with 1 cup sour cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, peas (thawed), cheese and dressing.
Top with bacon.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 3 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can decorate tops with more M&M's after coming out of oven.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 60.

title: cream cheese drop cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Place nuts on top, pressing into dough.
Bake from 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or hamburger or kielbasa sausage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with 1 package onion soup mix.
Cover with consomme soup or dissolved bouillon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: wesson pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients with fork until blended.
Form into a ball. Cut ball in half.
Roll out between two pieces of waxed paper. Peel top piece of paper off and turn rolled dough into pie plate. Repeat same process for top crust.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes for 22 to 24 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Slice a thin piece from top of each (discard) and carefully scoop out with a small spoon.
Make ranch dressing according to directions on package.
Mash potatoes with butter and enough ranch dressing
so potato mixture is still firm.
Mix in cheese.
Carefully put back into potato skins (mixture will pile out over top of potato).
You may freeze at this point, thaw and bake 30 minutes at 350° or bake right away for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Mix chicken, vegetables, soup and seasonings.
Spread into 9-inch pie shell.
Add shell on top. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain.
Add butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix together; then add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Cook in a greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: beef with snow peas
directions: In large
skillet,
over
medium heat, cook beef strips with onion in
hot
oil	until
beef is browned, stirring constantly. Stir
in
beef
broth, mushrooms with liquid, sherry and soy sauce.
Add
cornstarch to 1/4 cup water and mix well. Add to meat and
cook	until
mixture has thickened, stirring constantly. Add
snow
peas
and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Cook rabbit with several big slices of onion, salt and pepper until done.
If rabbit is wild the onion will take away the wildness.
Remove meat from bones and place in bottom of dough lined pie plate.
Add potatoes (finely sliced), carrots, celery and onions.
Top with salt and pepper to taste.
Add about 3 tablespoons of the broth that the rabbit had cooked in.
Cover with pie dough.
Pinch edges to seal and prick the top a few times with fork.
Bake at 350° for at least an hour or until potatoes are done.
Also good served with additional broth.

title: crab spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature about 1 hour.
Mix by hand, cream cheese and crab meat.
Dice onion and celery and mix in cream cheese and crab mixture.
Roll this mixture into a big, softball form.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle Old Bay all over this ball.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into an ungreased pie pan. Bake 30 min. at 350°.

title: turkey waldorf salad
directions: Chill ingredients.
Sprinkle diced apple with lemon juice.
Add turkey, grapes, celery, walnuts, onion, salad dressing, salt and pepper and toss lightly.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Cut white of egg into wedges and arrange in shape of a flower.
Top with grated yolk.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: orange coconut cookies for diabetics
directions: Combine saccharin, orange juice and vanilla.
Cream in margarine.
Sift in flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Knead in coconut.
Roll in "tube."
Chill.
Slice 1/8-inch thick. Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch pieces and boil until tender in salted water. Spray 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam and add crushed crackers to cover bottom of dish. Cover crackers with layer of cheese. Drain cooked squash and mix with sour cream, onion, salt, sugar and pepper. Spoon soupy mixture over crackers. Cover mixture with layer of crackers and then top with layer of cheese to thoroughly cover. Pour warm milk over mixture to moisten and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken a la mexican
directions: Rub chicken in combined seasonings.
Brown in shortening in skillet.
When nicely browned pour in Zippy Vegetable Sauce. Cover.
Simmer 35 to 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo; add salt and pepper to taste. Add corn, pimiento, and rice; stir together and place in a baking dish. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with onion, green pepper and garlic. Add remaining ingredients and put into casserole; cover with cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, butter and pecans; pat down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping; spread over cooled crust.
Beat together the lemon instant pudding and milk; spread over cheese filling.
Can put the rest of the whipped topping over the top.
Chill 12 hours.

title: boned chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken in seasoned flour.
Dip in beaten egg.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Dip in Parmesan cheese.
Fry chicken in hot butter-oleo (half and half).
Don't cover pan.
Fry until brown on both sides, 3 minutes per side or until brown and done.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until blended.
Shape into 3-inch patties.
Pour cooking oil in skillet until 1/4 inch full. Heat over medium heat until hot.
Slip 4 cakes into skillet.
Fry, turning over once.
Cook until golden brown, about 6 minutes. Transfer to paper toweling to dry.

title: american peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in bottom of pan (greased). Pour peaches and juice on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lethal layers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a food processor, combine first 3 ingredients with metal blade until crumbly.
(Can also be done with knives or pastry cutter.)
Pat crumbs into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
When crust is cool, spread pecans evenly over surface.
Beat eggs with brown sugar until thick.
Add vanilla.
Put baking powder and salt in bottom of 1/4 cup measure.
Fill rest of measure with flour.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until center is baked.
Cool; then cut into 32 pieces.
Enjoy!

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put shortening, salt and sugar in boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
When cooled, beat in four cups of the flour and the eggs; beat real good.
Add yeast.
Stir in the other 5 cups of flour; mix real good.
Leave out until doubled in bulk, then put in refrigerator until ready for use.
Set dough out before using to let it warm some.
Roll out on floured board; cut with cutter and dip in melted butter, before putting in pans.
Let rise until double in pans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Chop onion and green pepper. Combine ingredients and mix together. Put in baking dish and bake one hour. Glaze meat loaf with ketchup.

title: mock salmon cakes(fish patties)
directions: Combine all ingredients and make patties.
Fry in oil until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into pie crusts.
Garnish with peanuts.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Let boil for 1 minute or until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cool water.
Remove from heat and add oats.
Drop by round spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Put heavy-duty foil into pan.
Put meat on foil.
Mix rest of ingredients in blender and pour over meat.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bring foil up over meat.
Fold edges to seal tight.
Bake 2 hours or until very tender at 375°.
Also excellent when cooked in a slow cooker.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix and pour in roaster.
Cook in 250° to 300° oven until thick and glossy.
Makes about 7 to 8 pints.

title: sand tarts
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar and beat until light.
Add egg and orange rind.
Combine all and chill.
Roll thin, cut, brush with beaten egg white and water.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped cabbage au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook cabbage in boiling water until wilted, about 6 minutes.
Drain.
Combine tomatoes, sugar, paprika, salt and pepper, breaking up tomatoes with back of spoon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips on low heat. When melted, pour over cereal and stir until cereal is coated. Place powdered sugar in a large bag and add cereal, then shake.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and bring to a boil.
Add milk and bring to a boil again.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Beat several minutes and frost cake. Decorate with nuts.

title: cauliflower cheese souffle
directions: Add flour to melted butter in saucepan.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Cool.
Add egg yolks and cauliflower; mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Mix melted margarine and corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: wine biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make 4 pieces and roll and mix again.
Roll out by hand small pieces about the size of a cigarette and put 2 twist together 2 times.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or less.

title: cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Add flour and nuts.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on paper towels.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all of the ingredients with a mixer on medium speed or in a blender on low speed for 30 seconds.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve over mixed greens or use as a marinade.

title: cherry mountain candy
directions: Bring margarine, milk, sugar and marshmallows to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla chips, cherry extract and food coloring.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill while preparing topping.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread on top of other ingredients and cool in freezer.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place sliced chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Process first 3 ingredients in food processor, then add 1 cup sugar.
Chill overnight.

title: enchiladas ole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add tomato sauce and set aside. Have ready skillet with hot oil, pan of heated enchilada sauce, baking dish (13 x 9 x 3-inches), grated cheese, chopped ripe olives, 1/2 of the onions and hamburger mixture.
Dip tortilla in deep hot oil, then dip in sauce.
Put hamburger, cheese and olive on tortilla, roll up and put in baking dish.
Continue until all are done.
Cover with remaining enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake until cheese has melted.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.

title: caraway skillet slaw
directions: Saute bacon until crisp in a medium size frying pan. Drain on paper toweling and then crumble. Measure 1/4 cup bacon grease and return to pan. Stir in vinegar, onion, sugar and salt.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling. Stir in the shredded cabbage and caraway seed.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serve warm from the pan. Serves 4.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa and coffee.
Add softened margarine and vanilla. Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add sugar about 1/3 at a time. Beat until of spreading consistency.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate (or cocoa) in large double boiler; add sugar and beat well; add flour, beat.
Add nuts and vanilla. Last, add eggs and beat vigorously.
Pour in greased pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes in moderate oven.
(This recipe is better doubled but cook longer when doubling.)

title: pecan turtles
directions: On a sheet of wax paper, form 6 turtle-like shapes by using long pecan halves for legs and the crosswise pieces for heads. Grease a microwave-safe plate.
Place 6 caramels at a time around the outer edge of the plate and microwave on High for 15 or 20 seconds.
Press a warm caramel over each turtle shape.
Repeat process until you have 2 dozen Turtles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in casserole dish. Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm dressing crumbs to cover bottom.
Pour in squash mixture, then sprinkle rest of dressing crumbs on top. Bake 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon crazy bread
directions: Roll each biscuit into a ball; roll the ball in butter and then mix in the mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Layer rolls and nuts in rows in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately.

title: granny's chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine. Cook slowly to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add 1/2 stick margarine. Stir until creamy. Spread over cake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine cheese and sausage.
Add Bisquick and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook meat in oil with onion and garlic until lightly browned. Add chili powder, salt, pepper, catsup and cumin.
Stir well and cover over low heat for 20 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
In 10 x 12-inch pan, layer refried beans, cooked meat, green chilies and cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese layer.
You may cover and refrigerate at this point.
Cook, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and quickly spread green onion, olives, avocados and top with sour cream.
Serve with Doritos or cooked tortillas.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together first four ingredients until light and fluffy. Fold in Cool Whip until well blended.
Spoon into pie shell. Chill overnight.
Before serving, drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: fruit fritters
directions: *Or can use 3 medium firm ripe bananas, peeled and cut in 1/2 inch round slices or 4 to 5 medium apples, pared, cored and cut in 8 wedges.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add undrained pineapple.
Sift soda and flour together.
Grease and flour oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese, oleo, powdered sugar and chopped pecans.
Spread on warm cake.
May be prepared in advance and kept in freezer.

title: persimmon pudding(heritage)
directions: Mash and strain the persimmons.
Melt the butter in two large Pyrex baking dishes.
Mix all of the ingredients together and divide between the two dishes.
Bake slowly until done (dark brown).
Stir once or twice while baking.
Pudding will be stiff. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease a deep dish pie plate.
Layer broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender.
Pour into pie plate over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted halfway in center comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips; stir just well enough to distribute chips throughout mixture. Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together; set aside. Measure cereal and milk into a large bowl.
Stir to combine; let stand for 1 to 2 minutes until cereal is soft.
Add egg and shortening or vegetable oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated beef tenderloin
directions: Combine all liquid in small bowl and cover meat, turning to cover both sides.
Use 1/2 of dry seasonings on each side.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning every 6 hours. When ready to cook, remove from refrigerator for 30 minutes to allow to come to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Cook meat for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325°.
Keep covered with foil for about 20 minutes.
For medium rare, cook for 15 to 20 minutes per pound.
Baste the meat every 10 to 15 minutes.
Let meat sit for 15 minutes before cutting.
Take off fat and string.
Reserve the drippings to pour over the meat after it is carved.
For a main dish, a small beef tender will feed 6 and a large will feed 8.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and eggs until fluffy.
Add soda, cinnamon, flour and milk.
Fold in apples.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in pan and cover with wax paper and bake at 325° until done.

title: clam chowder
directions: Place green onions (chopped), celery, carrots and potatoes in chicken broth and simmer.
While this is simmering, make white sauce with butter and flour.
Melt butter, then stir in flour; blend until smooth.
Gradually add milk (if too thick, add more milk).
After this thickens, add cream of mushroom soup.
Blend together.
After the vegetable mixture is tender, add white sauce to vegetables.
Add clams and enjoy!

title: tangy cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup pecans in an oiled 7-cup ring mold and press cheese mixture into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, pull meat from bone.
Mix well with stuffing and cream of chicken soup.
Put into greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except lemon-lime soda and freeze.
When ready to use, add lemon-lime soda.

title: cranberry salad 1
directions: Heat cranberry sauce.
Strain and save juice.
Dissolve jello in water and add cranberry juice, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until thick enough to mold.
Beat in mayonnaise.
Fold in cranberry sauce, nuts and orange or apple.
Chill until set.

title: stir-fried brussels sprouts with tangerines
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts 5 minutes in boiling water; drain them. Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Stir-fry Brussels sprouts, onion, caraway seed and bouillon 5 minutes.
(Add 1/4 cup water if bouillon does not dissolve readily.)
Add tangerine segments and mushrooms and heat through.

title: campbell's super burgers
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions.
Add next four ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on the buns.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet; press with fork, making design on top.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Set oven at 375°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix together noodles, tuna, cheese, soup, milk, peas, salt, pepper and onion powder.
Dot margarine on top of mixture, then cover with Italian bread crumbs.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: delicious salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients, starting with lettuce and ending with carrots.
Spread salad dressing over carrots.
Top with cheese, then bacon bits.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all together and let set for about 1 hour; mix again. (Repeat 3 or 4 times.)

title: caramel icing
directions: Place the 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet over low heat.
In saucepan, mix the 2 cups sugar, milk, butter and slightly beaten egg.
Stir over low heat until butter melts.
Increase heat and cook until it boils rapidly.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and dry salad dressing mix.
Blend well. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese mixture over one ham slice; repeat with three more ham slices, ending with cream cheese mixture.
Roll up; place rolls in covered container and refrigerate.
Before serving, thinly slice each roll.
Serve on crackers.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise in 1/4 inch rounds.
Season with salt and pepper,
Roll in bread crumbs.
Dip into beaten eggs.
Roll again in bread crumbs.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Fry in oil until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Line a 2 qt. baking dish with some sauce, put layer of eggplant slices on sauce, sprinkle with basil, parmesan and oregano, top with a layer of mozzarella.
Then repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and pineapple in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add 3/4 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt; stir well.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Roll in remaining 1/4 cup pecans.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and spices together several times.
Mix egg yolks, oil, water and caraway seed in large bowl. Add dry ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds at low speed.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Gradually pour egg mixture over beaten whites and gently fold in.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Increase heat to 350° for 15 minutes more.
Invert pan on rack and cool cake.

title: creole corn pudding
directions: Grate the corn and mix it with the tepid milk.
Whip the whole eggs into a froth and add these and the other ingredients to the corn and milk.
The yeast powder comes last.
Bake in a slow oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: white frosting
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, butter and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: homemade cocoa
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on can.
Chill.
Add equal parts of Kool-Aid to equal parts of chilled ginger ale.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa in a small saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Combine chocolate mixture, sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Add flour, nuts, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Immediately top with marshmallows and cover with Chocolate Frosting.
Let cool.

title: taco salad i
directions: Crumble ground beef into skillet; brown. Drain well and let cool. Place all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: bubble buns
directions: Grease 10 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In small bowl, combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Separate biscuits.
Cut into quarters; shape into balls.
Coat each with mayonnaise, then roll in walnut mixture.
Place 4 in each muffin pan cup.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 17 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 10.

title: deviled potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but not mushy. Cool and peel.
Boil eggs and cool with cold water.
Set aside.
Separate out yolks and mash until very mealy.
Combine with Miracle Whip, sour cream and mustard. Mix well.

title: chewy fruit cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle on nuts, dates, fruit and coconut.
Pour milk on top and bake 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: fish stew
directions: Boil fish; remove bones.
Add potatoes, onions and celery. Fry bacon; add bacon and grease to fish broth; boil until done. Add soup, catsup, salt, pepper, Texas Pete and fish.
Simmer for 20 minutes; stir often.

title: black walnut or pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients, except nuts, with the mix.
Mix in nuts. Pour in crusts and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, butter and eggs.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Add first four ingredients together.
Combine shortening and sugar, cream well.
Blend in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix well.
Add pecans, dates and cherries, mix well.
Shape into balls using a level tablespoonful of dough for each cookie.
You can roll in crushed cornflakes if you want to. Place on greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 cherry. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple chunks.
Save juice. Dissolve jello in hot water and set aside juice.
Add fruit and marshmallows when jello begins to thicken.
Pour into rectangular dish and cover with topping.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook onion and celery slowly in margarine.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix carefully.
Place in greased crock-pot.
Cook on high for 15 minutes, then on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Can also be baked in oven.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Remove leaves and remove core from cauliflower.
In covered saucepan, cook whole cauliflower in a small amount of boiling salted water 20 to 25 minutes until just tender when tested with fork.
Drain well and chill.
Place chilled cauliflower on platter.
Garnish platter with radish roses.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Beat until batter is smooth.
Stir in coconut and fold in stiffened beaten egg whites.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: four cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine noodles and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: grizzle knuckles(cookies)
directions: Roll crackers (approximately 27 to 30) into crumbs.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly since the mixture is thick.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Don't let it get too brown on edges.)
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: noodle bake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Brown chop meat and drain.
Add chopped up onion and green pepper.
Add tomato soup and simmer all together for 45 minutes, stirring once in a while.
Boil noodles.
When ready pour chop meat mixture on bottom of pan and add noodles on top.
Spread evenly.
Add thin slices of American cheese on top here and there.
Bake until hot or for 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!

title: hot turkey (or chicken) salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and lightly place in pans.
Sprinkle 3 pounds grated Cheddar cheese on top of mixture.
Cover with 14 ounces crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pudding and gelatin over mixture.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bachelor's easy lemon cheese pie
directions: Bake crust if required.
Cool.
Add 1/2 cup milk to softened cream cheese.
Cream until smooth.
Add the remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and the lemon pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix food coloring with butter
and syrup.
Mix with peppermint and sugar with hands.
Put into molds.
Pop out.
Let dry overnight.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: weight watchers chicken hunter style
directions: Broil the chicken for 10 minutes on each side.
Combine the next 10 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups of water and 2 tablespoons red wine vinegar (optional). Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: grilled fish steaks with lime butter
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan on stove top or barbecue grill. Stir in lime juice and thyme leaves; mix well.
Heat barbecue so that coals are very hot.
Grill fish over hot coals for 5 minutes on first side.
Baste occasionally with lime butter; turn fish and brush again.
Grill for another 5 minutes.
Serve fish garnished with lime slices and thyme sprigs.
Makes 8 servings.

title: junk casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together in large skillet.
Boil potatoes.
Put ground beef and potatoes in casserole dish.
Add Cheddar cheese soup, mushroom soup and water.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinara sauce
directions: In a deep 10-inch frying pan, heat olive oil and saute garlic. Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Put on medium heat 20 to 30 minutes, occasionally stirring.
Tear basil leaves and sprinkle on top.
This is a light sauce and goes great not only with pasta but with seafood and chicken.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt as for any crust.
Beat egg. Add water and vinegar and add to flour mixture.
Roll out at room temperature.
Makes 3 to 4 crusts.

title: beer bread
directions: Grease loaf pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients and place in loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 1 loaf.

title: lo-fat double chocolate biscotti(ideal for kitchenaid-type mixer; adapted from "gourmet")
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray and flour baking sheet with low calorie baking spray.
Blend dry ingredients and set aside.
In large bowl beat together applesauce, butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, until combined.
Blend flour mixture to form stiff dough; add chips (and nuts).
Halve dough to form two, gently-flattened logs about 12 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake for 35 minutes or until slightly firm to the touch.
Cool briefly for 5 minutes.
Transfer to cutting board (save the baking sheets, "biscotti" means twice baked in Italian). Slice diagonally into 3/4 inch slices.
Arrange biscotti cut-sides down on baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Cool on rack; store in airtight container.
Re-crisp at 300° for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: italian salad
directions: Break vermicelli into small pieces before cooking. Cook until tender in salted water. Drain well. Mix other ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, cut into small pieces and mix with vermicelli, tomato, onion and green pepper.

title: tossed pasta salad
directions: Cut and blanch vegetables.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Prepare dressing.
Put together and toss.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve with assorted crackers.

title: aunt b's grape-nut bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let sit for 1 hour.
Beat and add to remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 35-40 min.

title: beans and rice
directions: Saute onions and sausage in 2 Tbsp. oil; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Heat chocolate	and coffee (or cognac) in top of double boiler.
As
soon
as
water
boils, remove top pan from heat. Stir the
chocolate
mixture until very smooth and glossy.	In medium bowl,
mix
yolks until thick and pale.
Gradually beat in chocolate.

title: roast beef sandwich
directions: Place roast beef and cheese between two slices of bread. Butter outsides and grill.
Season with mayonnaise and horseradish.

title: lemon explosive
directions: Put everything together in a shaker.
Serve with ice and cherry.
Refreshing!

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Place in well-greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over biscuits.
Drizzle margarine over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine all but popcorn in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat to 220° (full boil).
Remove.
Let cool.
Pour on popcorn.
Butter hands and shape into balls.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Use 1/2 part Dijon mustard to 1/4 parts honey and white rice vinegar.
Add black pepper and other spices as desired.
Mix in large bowl and chill.
Serve over salad or as a dip.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together and cook in rice steamer until done.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, folding in the Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice thinly.
Combine cucumbers, onions, green pepper, garlic and salt in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables. Add celery, onion and kidney beans. Cook the remaining ingredients until thickened. Cool and mix with the vegetables.

title: sauce tomato with rice
directions: Cut up carrots in slices.
Cut up onions in small pieces.
Cut up tomatoes; take out seeds (optional).
Mash the tomatoes.
Cut up beef into pieces.
Cut up cabbage in thin slices.
Put 2/3 cup of oil in casserole.
When hot, put in onions; stir.
Put in garlic clove, meat and tomatoes.
Cook until all the water is used up, then put in 3 cups of water.
Put in tomato sauce, cabbage, carrots, green beans and noodles.
Cook 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Then put in salt and bouillon cubes.
Serve on bed of cooked rice.

title: fisherman's bowl
directions: Saute celery with garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir now and then, being careful not to scorch.
Serves 6.

title: "baby doe's" beer cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring milk to simmering point.
Add chicken stock, Cheddar cheese and other ingredients, except cornstarch and beer.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Make thin cornstarch paste by adding water to cornstarch and use to thicken the soup.

title: keep forever slaw - ii
directions: Shred cabbage and vegetables to your liking.
Pour dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate.
This recipe keeps well for several days.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well and chill.
Reserve 1 cup for top and sides.
Put remainder between layers.
Combine reserved cup with Cool Whip; blend until smooth.
Frost cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in casserole.
Cover with pineapple and then cake mix sprinkled on top.
Melt 2 sticks oleo; pour over top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
You can add nuts to this cake if desired.
Serve with ice cream, Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Dissolve sugars in cream and boil to the thread test (228°), stirring occasionally.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook until syrup reaches soft ball test.
Cool; beat until somewhat thickened but not until it loses its gloss.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto double thickness waxed paper.
Candy will flatten into large cakes.
Makes 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Drain.
Beat egg yolks with milk and gradually add flour.
Stir in corn.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Beat egg whites until very frothy and stiff.
Add to corn mixture.
Put sausages in bottom of casserole dish and pour corn mixture over.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook meat and onion until meat is browned, stirring constantly.
Drain completely. Stir in the rest of the ingredients and serve warm or cold.
Great with hamburger buns or crackers.

title: kale soup
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight; drain.

Add onion, pepperoni, kale, salt, pepper, vinegar and 10 cups of water. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Add potatoes and 1 cup water and cook until potatoes are done.

title: spiced macadamia nuts
directions: *Can also use pecans or almonds.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together and set aside.

title: french canadian meat pie
directions: In large pot put ground beef and all of the above ingredients; add approximately 1 c. water and cook on medium heat for about 1 hour stirring frequently.

title: jo william's salsa
directions: Toss all ingredients together; add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with all your Mexican dishes.

title: nutty brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable oil or cooking spray.
Put oats in blender and blend for 1 minute.
Combine margarine and cocoa in a separate bowl.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, flour and remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes for chewy brownies or 17 minutes for cake-like brownies.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sirloin steak and gravy(microwave)
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and put in an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Arrange onion and lemon slices over meat. Cream butter and prepared mustard; blend in chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and vegetable juice. Pour mixture over onion and lemon.

title: watergate salad
directions: Do not prepare pudding.
Pour Jell-O as boxed into bowl and combine all ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Serve.

title: mrs. tom triplett's red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of cake coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt to flour and sift.
Add flour and buttermilk; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add soda and vinegar.
Do not beat, just blend.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt pie
directions: Place Oreos
in
a large Ziploc bag and beat senseless. Place Oreo
crumbs
into food processor and grind to a powder. Set aside Oreo
crumbs.
In
a
food processor cream together margarine and
cream cheese, mixing well.
Add powdered sugar to cream cheese
mixture and mix well.
Add milk and continue mixing
until completely
combined.
Add dry pudding mix next and mix well. Add Cool Whip last and fold in until mixture is smooth.
In
large pan pat 1/2 of the Oreo crumbs in bottom of pan.
Spoon
cream cheese mixture over Oreos and add remaining Oreo crumbs on top.

title: kielbasa and white kidney beans
directions: Brown
sausage	in heavy 4 quart heatproof casserole or ovenproof
Dutch oven over medium heat.
Stir in celery, onion and carrot;
cook
5 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add beans,
broth and pepper.	Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: lobster stew
directions: Combine lobsters and butter and let stand 4 hours.
Heat cream and milk in double boiler to almost scald.
Add to lobster, which is warm.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh melon balls, strawberries, pineapple chunks, sliced bananas, Red Delicious apple slices and mandarin oranges.
Don't forget the toothpicks.

title: mary's grape and banana salad
directions: Wash grapes and cut in half.
Peel and slice bananas.
Mix grapes, bananas, marshmallows and nuts.
Add dressing.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over kraut mixture and let set overnight before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: crab - shrimp mold
directions: Heat 1 can tomato soup.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water. Add gelatine to soup; remove from heat.
Beat in cream cheese until well blended.
Add mayonnaise.
Stir in onion, celery and green pepper, then shrimp or crab.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: chicken manicotti (healthmark)
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, bring tomato juice, garlic, 3/4 of the combined seasonings and pepper to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer mixture 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
On cutting board, pound chicken pieces to about 1/4-inch thickness; set aside.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour until well blended.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and puree in a food processor.
Add peanut butter and cream, stirring to blend thoroughly.
Return to heat until just hot, but do not boil.

title: jambalaya pasta
directions: In skillet, saute onion, peppers and celery in butter until tender. Stir in tomatoes, broth, mushrooms and seasonings. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw(heart healthy)
directions: In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar together. In a large bowl, mix cabbage, carrots and onions. Add mayonnaise mixture to the vegetable mixture. Chill and serve.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix together.
Pour into crust.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in a roaster.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Pour over ribs.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours covered.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: breakfast enchiladas
directions: Mix ham, onion, green pepper and cheese together.
Place in flour tortillas.
Roll.
Mix the milk, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: mom's pork chop skillet dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in olive oil in large skillet. Add potatoes, onions and carrots to skillet. In medium bowl, combine undiluted soup and brown sugar. Pour over pork chop mixture, coating all ingredients evenly. Cover and cook on simmer for 30 to 45 minutes (until potatoes and carrots are tender). Stir occasionally. Serves 4.

title: festive punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until dissolved. Then add remaining ingredients to first mixture. Will make approximately four gallons. After pouring in punch bowl, add 1 bottle of ginger ale for each gallon of punch. Add food coloring to get the right shade of color. Make 24 hours ahead of time and freeze. Take out of freezer on the morning you plan to serve. Really good.

title: scalloped potatoes with celery soup
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Thin out celery soup a little with milk or water.
In greased pan, line layer of potatoes.
Add soup.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and bread crumbs to each layer.
Repeat until all ingredients are consumed.
Bake in oven at 450° without lid for 1/2 hour.
When mixture comes to a boil, lower temperature to 350° until potatoes are done.
Place pork chops on top, if desired.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Dump the fruit and juices into bowl.
Add pudding.
Stir until thickened.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugars and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips, and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Blanch cabbage in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cut in wedges, discarding the head parts.
Dice the pork and saute in large saucepan for 5 minutes.
Dice
2 of the onions and saute in pan for a few minutes.
Add cabbage and garlic.
Add the broth and the remaining onion studded with the cloves.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, frankfurters and honey.
Cook until potatoes are very tender.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in slow cooker for 4 to 5 hours on medium.

title: ground meat dish
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, salt and pepper to taste, oregano and some red pepper.
Pour into dish with tomatoes, water and bay leaf.
Mix with cooked rice.
Push this mixture into top of bell pepper rings.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: peppermint punch
directions: Spoon ice cream into a large punch bowl.
Add egg nog and chilled club soda, mixing well.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, enough to give punch a pink color, and stir.
Serve punch topped with whipped cream.
Sprinkle whipped cream with crushed candy and place a small peppermint stick in each cup as a stirring stick.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat slowly and drain. Brown sausage slowly and drain. Melt cheese in top of double boiler. Add meat mixture to melted cheese. Add tomatoes and green chillies and garlic salt. Serve warm with chips. Serves 12.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Mix all together.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut each layer in half.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in pieces, including stems.
Add onions, bacon and cubed/shredded cheese.
Set aside.

title: chicken with curry sauce
directions: Cover chicken breasts with kosher salt and black pepper. Saute in olive oil until browned.
Put in a 350° oven until chicken is cooked through.
Mix remaining ingredients except curry powder.
Chop apples to 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook sauce until thickened; add curry powder and continue cooking.
When chicken is done, top with sauce.
Serve.

title: english apple pie
directions: Butter or grease 9-inch pie dish.
Pour in 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Slice in apples, heaped to rim of dish.
Mix butter, flour and brown sugar together (will be crumbly).
Place on top of apples.
Pat firmly.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, until topping bubbles.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: kay's bundt cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Add oil and water.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Add both flavorings.
Beat 6 to 7 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan well and sprinkle half of nut and sugar mixture in pan (coat all over as if it were flour).
Pour half of batter into pan.
Sprinkle rest of mixture
over batter.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Check to see if done; it may take 55 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will be soft.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute; remove to rack to cool completely.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Combine in a glass bowl with onions, sliced thin.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours.
Pour in colander and let drain.
In an 8 to 10-quart pan, combine vinegar and rest of the ingredients.
Bring to boil; add cucumbers and onions.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Pack hot in hot jars.
Seal. Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin, then peel potatoes and cube them. Mix all ingredients with potatoes.
Serve on a platter of lettuce.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with beater until creamy.
Put in bowl.
Shred lettuce, chop tomatoes, shred sharp cheese and chop the black olives.
Layer these on top of dip in listed order. Serve with nacho chips.

title: sweet and sour dill chips
directions: Slice pickle thin.
Add 3 or 4 slices onion, 2 pieces celery and 2 heads of dill per jar.
Place pickles in jars.
Add onion, celery and dill on top each jar.
Cover with brine.
Process 5 minutes.

title: v.b.s.  chocolate chip cookies
directions: In very large bowl, add butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; add eggs and beat well.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 minutes at 375°.
Yield: Approximately 15 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put cubed bread in pan sprayed with Pam.
Next, add cooked and drained sausage.
Mix cheese, eggs, milk, mustard and soup together; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight; drain.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Boil 30 minutes.
Drain and add water again to make 8 quart pot about 3/4 full.
Add onions and ham.
Cook slowly at least two hours.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mash some of the beans before serving.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Cool.
Mix beaten egg, flour, sugar, salt and cocoa (melted in hot water).
Cook in double boiler until creamy. Cool.
Add flavoring and beat with beater.

title: spicy ham balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and shape into 10 to 12 balls.
Mix the next four ingredients together and bring to a boil. Pour over meat balls and bake at 350°.

title: shrimp saute
directions: In small bowl, mix water, soy sauce, cornstarch, bouillon and ginger; set aside.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook shrimp, peppers and water chestnuts in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green onions and cornstarch mixture; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 10 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Serve hot.
I usually serve with rice.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Add the cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Place mixture in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon lime curd
directions: In a heavy saucepan whisk together the sugar, the whole eggs, the yolks, the juices and the zests. Cook the mixture over moderately low heat, whisking, until the sugar is dissolved.
Add the butter, cook the mixture over low heat, whisking, for 10-12 minutes, or until it registers 160° on a candy thermometer. Transfer to glass jars.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: In a 2-quart micro-proof dish, stir together milk and cornstarch until cornstarch dissolves completely.
Stir in sugar, Sweet One, cocoa and salt.
Cook at 100% power (High), stirring several times, for 6 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into individual serving dishes and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Makes 5 (1/2-cup) servings.
Calories:
125 per serving.
Calories saved:
245 per serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, juice and rind.
Add egg yolks; mix well and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add 4 tablespoons sugar, beating constantly.
Swirl meringue on top of filling.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage rings
directions: Mix and roll Bisquick as directed for biscuits.
Roll out sausage between 2 pieces of aluminum foil or Saran Wrap to approximately same size as rolled biscuit dough.
Turn sausage onto dough and roll end to end.
Wrap roll in aluminum foil and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and place on cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Great as a breakfast food or party appetizer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and mix with 2 cups corn flakes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute ground beef with onion.
Add garlic salt and the next five ingredients.
Mix well.
In a 3-quart loaf pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan, alternate layers of tortillas and meat mixture, ending with meat mixture.
Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes.
Remove cover and add cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Beat until stiff and fold into the pumpkin mixture.
Pour over the cooled baked cheese cake layer.
Let stand until firm and then top with a small carton Cool Whip or a package Dream Whip, prepared according to package directions.
Refrigerate.

title: sage dressing
directions: Fry sausage, onion and celery.
Break toast into mixing bowl. Add meat mixture, sage, soup, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix.
Add hot water as needed to moisten.
Bake until set, about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: play dough
directions: Heat all ingredients over medium heat on stove.
Stir while cooking until play dough is stiff.
Knead and cool.
Store in airtight container.
Great for all ages!
Dries fast on carpets for easy pick up!
Doesn't matter if the children get some in their mouths; it's edible!!

title: mostaccioli
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add and brown ground beef and onion.
Pour noodles in boiling water to cover and let cook until almost dry.
Add tomatoes, spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add olive oil and simmer.
Layer noodles and sauce in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and serve hot.

title: roasted garlic cloves
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
