Break garlic head into cloves.
Leave the inner skins on the cloves.
Put garlic in small ovenproof dish and add the olive oil, thyme and bay leaf.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.

title: cucumber yogurt dip
directions: Blend together and chill at least one hour.

title: mandarin orange-lettuce salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: french bistro cake
directions: Sift powdered sugar and flour together.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and almond until peaks form.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in flour mixture slowly.
Spoon into two 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Beat whipping cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
(Chill bowl, whipping cream and beaters first.)
Place 1 cake layer on plate.
Spread top with half cream and half of fruit.
Place next layer on top and spread with remaining cream, then decorate with remaining fruit. Refrigerate until served.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni or noodles until tender and drain.
Mix soup, milk and salt; heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into 2-quart casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven 400°. Mix flour and whipping cream. Pour on floured wax paper. Knead and roll until 1/2-inch thick. Cook in preheated oven until golden brown.

title: main dish salad
directions: Bring peas, salt and water to a boil.
Boil covered for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice and cover tightly.
Let stand until cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Mix this with the creamed mixture.
Crush cookies in blender.
Put half of cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the mixture over the cookies.
Cover with remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze 12 hours and put in refrigerator to thaw.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 1 hour; remove chicken from bones.
Lay in bottom of casserole dish.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Drain clams, reserving 3/4 cup liquid; set aside.
In medium skillet, slowly heat oil and butter.
Add garlic and saute until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam liquid, parsley and salt; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add clams; simmer 3 minutes.
Serve hot over spaghetti.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in water as directed on package.
Let cool.
Brown bacon in skillet until crisp.
Beat eggs in bowl; scramble in small amount of bacon grease.
Add bacon and eggs to rice.
Mix well.
Add chopped onion; mix well.
Add soy sauce; mix well. Cook in nonstick pan for about 15 minutes.
You may use any leftovers: pork, ham or beef.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring Coca-Cola, margarine, cocoa and oil to a boil.
Pour over a mixture of the sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pecans, cinnamon and 4 teaspoons sugar; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Fold in vanilla, almond and sour cream.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Fold into mixture.
Place about 1/3 batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan. Sprinkle with 3/4 of the pecan mixture.
Spoon in remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining pecan mix.
Bake about 65 minutes. Cool on rack for 20 minutes before turning out on plate.

title: frozen cream cheese cake
directions: Blend first three ingredients well, then add pineapple and rest.
Blend well.
Freeze.
Un-freeze to serve.
Can be refrozen.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and chop fine.
Saute onion and celery in butter; stir in soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add cooked rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
For best results, prepare a day ahead and refrigerate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine cake mix, peanut butter, eggs and milk in a large bowl; mix at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in Reese's Pieces or peanut butter chips.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet; remove to cooling rack. Yields 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients and pour into large 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain and place in bottom of casserole dish. Cover with double layer of corn tortillas, torn into small pieces. Add more onion, if desired.
Cover with grated cheese.
Mix soup with tomatoes and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with more cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be cooked in microwave until mixture is hot and bubbly.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Simmer vegetables 10 to 15 minutes. Add beaten eggs and stir until eggs are cooked and stringy. Garnish with chopped green onions and a few drops of soy sauce and sesame oil.

title: snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together.
Roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, turning over once at 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar when hot.
Roll a few more times in 10x sugar to taste (more times rolled, sweeter taste).

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except almonds.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate. Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased layer pans or 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: the ultimate tortilla soup
directions: In large pot boil chicken, onion, celery, bell pepper in water until chicken is done.
Remove chicken to cool and cut up in small pieces.
While cooling add garlic, cumin, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, garlic salt, and tomatoes to chicken broth and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Then added chopped chicken and mushrooms and simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Meanwhile, brown tortillas in nonstick griddle using spray oil.
After browned, cut into thin strips and put into bottom of soup bowls. Ladle in soup and serve with toppers.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine juice, butter and egg together.
Then mix together with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: squash with apple
directions: Bake squash and peeled apple until done.
Scoop out squash. In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add squash, apple, thyme, brown sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mash to make chunky puree.
Cover and heat through.

title: quick chili
directions: Mince garlic and combine with onion and ground meat in 2-quart microwave casserole dish.
Microwave, covered, for 3 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Drain meat and keep in casserole dish.
Rinse can of beans in colander and add beans to dish with meat.
Add can of tomatoes; don't drain. Coarsely cut tomatoes in dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir; microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High.
For soupier chili, add 1/2 cup water before microwaving.

title: oriental seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet until hot.
Add crab delights and vegetables.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasonings; stir well.
Cook 1 minute more.
Serve immediately.

title: buffalo chicken dip
directions: Drain and shred chicken; put into frying pan. Pour in hot sauce and completely coat chicken. Cut up cream cheese and melt in pot with chicken and hot sauce. Pour in Blue cheese dressing; cook 15 minutes. Add shredded cheese and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: microwave quiche lorraine
directions: Press rice evenly on bottom and sides of pie plate to form "shell".
Combine all other ingredients in measuring cup and heat thoroughly (3 minutes on High and 3 on Medium).
Pour into pie plate.
Microwave, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 40% power. Quiche will be almost set in middle.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator and is good cold.

title: rhubarb and pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pastry. Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes. Place pastry in 9-inch pie plate and add the filling. Fit remaining pastry on top; seal and flute the edge. Cut slits in top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling bubbly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican lasagna(makes 8 servings)
directions: In heavy skillet, brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and simmer until sauce thickens.

title: candied yams and fried apples
directions: Combine apples and yams.
Put into shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over entire casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally with the syrup in the casserole.

title: crab spread
directions: Chop onion fine; add garlic.
Mix onion, garlic, cheese and milk until blended.
Spread in shallow serving dish.
Coarsely chop tomato and green pepper.
Chop parsley finely.
Mix parsley, lemon juice, salt and vegetables.
Spoon on top of cheese mixture.
Top with crab meat.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley. Chill well.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.
Contains 21 calories per tablespoon.

title: easy angel food
directions: Break up angel food cake into bite-sized pieces and spread into bottom of 13 X 9 dish.
Sprinkle half of pineapple with juice over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box and pour over cake and pineapple.
Slice bananas and layer on top.
Add remaining pineapple and juice.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to one hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Grease casserole dish. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Delicious! Easy to double.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems and reserve for sauce.
Sprinkle mushroom caps with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients except sauce.
Pile ground beef mixture generously into mushrooms.
Place into shallow dish.
Bake about 45 minutes, basting every 5 minutes with sauce (beef stock). Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hoosier apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Sift flour, spices, soda and baking powder.
Mix well with first mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350°. Remove from oven and top with 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, mixed with 1 stick butter.
Return to oven and bake for about 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Beat chicken out fairly thin.
Place parsley and a square of butter in the middle.
Wrap chicken around the parsley and butter and put a toothpick through the middle to hold it together.
Then wrap the chicken with foil.
Drop chicken in a kettle of hot grease for approximately 5 minutes.

title: pork in orange-mustard sauce
directions: Cut pork in 1-inch cubes.
Spray Pam in large skillet and brown pork 15 minutes.
Add onion and garlic, stirring frequently until onions are slightly wilted.

title: chicken normandie
directions: Mix together croutons, margarine, water and salt.
Put 1/2 in greased glass pan 12 x 9-inches.
Set aside the rest of the mixture.
Mix together diced chicken, 1/2 teaspoon salt, celery, salad dressing, onions and pimentos.
Put in casserole over bread mixture, then top with remaining crouton mixture.
Combine eggs and milk and pour evenly over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out one hour before baking.
Spread mushroom soup over top.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits and pour milk over them.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix eggs, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add to biscuit mixture.
Mix well and pour into an 8-inch square baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook until mixture will form a soft ball in
cold
water.
Turn off heat, but leave on stove and add last three ingredients.
Stir until well blended and mixture begins to harden.
Pour onto aluminum foil immediately or if preferred
onto
a
buttered platter.
Let harden; slice and enjoy.

title: cajun peanut tongue-teasers
directions: Combine cheese, sesame seeds, paprika and cayenne pepper in mixing bowl. Set aside. Beat egg white until frothy. Add peanuts, tossing to coat. Add peanuts to cheese mixture; mix well. Spread single layer of nuts on lightly oiled baking sheet. Bake in preheated 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes, until golden. Cool, then serve, or store in airtight container.

title: crab ragoon
directions: Mix crab, cream cheese, green onion and garlic.
Mix.
Put in wonton wrapper.
Seal with egg whites.
Deep fry.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt, vanilla and pecans together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add vanilla just before it reaches the hard ball stage. Stir in pecans and coat well. Spoon onto waxed paper or brown paper and separate.

title: corn scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Mix and pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar; stir in egg, dates and raisins.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with apple butter.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: waccamaw salad(or 7 layer salad)
directions: Line clear glass salad bowl with eggs up to halfway.
Fill 1/2 bowl with lettuce.
Layer onion and peas (1/2 of each).
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar (1/2 of each).
Layer bacon, eggs and cheese.
Repeat.
Spread enough mayonnaise on top to completely cover salad and seal top.

title: brown candy
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar into black iron skillet and place over low heat until melted and light
brown in color.
Do not burn. Stir constantly with wooden
spoon.
Do	not
cook
fast.
It takes about 15 minutes
of
constant
stirring (but it's worth it).

title: pasta with mozzarella-tomato sauce
directions: Cut the tomatoes into 1/2-inch cubes and place them in a medium glass bowl.
Cut the Mozzarella into 1/2-inch cubes and add to the tomatoes.
Layer the basil leaves and then roll up lengthwise. Slice thinly through the roll to make a chiffonade and add to the tomato mixture.
Add the garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper to the bowl and stir to combine.
Allow to sit, covered, at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
When ready, cook the pasta in boiling salted water until al dente.
Drain and immediately toss with the raw tomato mixture.
Serve at once with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and more black pepper if desired.

title: quick and easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles and add butter, soup, tuna, milk and peas.
Stir until well mixed.

title: brown spaghetti
directions: Brown seasoned ground meat in large skillet.
Add onion soup mix.
Add just enough water to thicken.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add enough water to keep mixture thick.
Mix with hot spaghetti.
Serve.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine the milk and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until the marshmallows and chocolate chips are melted.
Fudge will be soft.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add onion, rice and spices. Also add soup and ketchup. Simmer 1/2 hour, stirring, as it will stick.
Add corn.
Let simmer until all the juices are gone. Stuff peppers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover tops with shredded Jack cheese and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Note:
May substitute 2 cans (18 ounces each) canned sweet potatoes.

title: house of grace tea
directions: In large pitcher, add tea and sugar. Then add juices and water. Stir briskly and serve over ice.

title: crabmeat pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, horseradish, lemon juice, onion and mayo with electric mixer and chill.
Right before serving, top with crabmeat and chili sauce.
Serve in pie plate with crackers on side.

title: rose petal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease muffin pans.
Spoon each 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes. Make and keep mixture in refrigerator several days to bake later.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Make 12 to 24 hours ahead of time needed to enhance flavor.
Keep refrigerated.
Great for raw vegetables or chips!

title: hot shrimp sandwiches
directions: Butter the bread on both sides. Place 4 slices of the bread in an 8-inch square glass pan. Combine shrimp, celery, onion, lemon juice, worcestershire sauce and soup. Spoon over bread. Top with cheese and remaining bread.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine half the onions, jalapeno and cilantro in a mortar or food processor; season with 1/2 tsp. salt, then grind or pulse into a smooth paste.
Place in a serving bowl.
Cut avocado in half lengthwise, then remove and discard pit.
Make crosshatch incisions in avocado pulp with a paring knife.
Scoop pulp out with a spoon, then combine with onion mixture.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining onions, jalapeno and cilantro, then gently mix in tomatoes.
Adjust seasoning with salt and serve immediately.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup of crushed crackers.
Then, mix all of the above ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle reserved cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at
350° for 1 hour.

title: beer battered onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender (except onions).
Refrigerate overnight.
Blend again and dip the sliced onions into mixture and deep fry.

title: orange sunset(makes 1 serving)
directions: In a tall glass, combine orange juice and lemon-lime soda. Pour grenadine in and let it sink to the bottom. Garnish with a maraschino cherry and a straw for stirring.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend vegetable oil, sugar and eggs well.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon together; add to sugar mixture at intervals.
Add vanilla and chopped apples.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: andrew's favorite snackin' crackers
directions: Combine vegetable oil and dressing mix.
Pour over oyster crackers in large bowl and stir to coat crackers.
Let stand 10 minutes and stir again.
Repeat 2 more times.
Great for snacks, in soup, or as croutons on a salad.

title: good "n" plenty skillet dinner
directions: In a large pot or heavy saucepan with lid, cook hamburger meat until it is no longer red.
Break up meat with a spoon as it cooks.
Add some onions and garlic (1 or 2 cloves) while cooking.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine milk and soups on medium heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in rice and bacon and heat thoroughly.

title: hobo soup
directions: Cook hamburger until browned.
Drain off fat.
Add 1 quart water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
May add corn, peas, green beans or other vegetables.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel, dice, parboil and drain zucchini.
In saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter and add Stove Top seasoning mix.
Add this to zucchini, sour cream, carrots, soup and 1/2 of Stove Top dressing crumbs.
Mix well.
Put in greased casserole.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter; add remaining half of Stove Top dressing crumbs; mix until moist.
Put on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg and sausage dish
directions: Fry sausage, then cut in half and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put bread on top.
Beat eggs with milk; pour on top of bread.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese (shredded).
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bear squares
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix cereal and 1 cup of marshmallows in a large bowl.
Put peanut butter, butter and the remaining marshmallows in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until completely melted and smooth.
Immediately pour over cereal mixture and stir until well blended.
Mixture will leave sides of pan and form a ball.
Transfer to prepared pan and press into an even layer.

title: dina's hamburger barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart pot.
Cook over low heat, stirring often to keep from burning, until meat is done and onion is soft, about 30 minutes.

title: jackie's 15 minute cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, pudding mix and condensed milk.
Hand mix until smooth and creamy.
Pour half of mixture into each pie crust.
Put half of topping on each pie.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and slice potatoes into 1/4-inch thick ovals, then slice ovals lengthwise in wedges.
Combine potatoes, egg whites and cinnamon in large bowl.
Pour coated potatoes into well-greased baking sheet and cook on bottom rack of oven.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 400°, until wedges are crispy, turning once.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Mix with oil, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
When dough is thawed, flatten to the shape of a football and spread with broccoli.
Evenly sprinkle cheese on broccoli.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Beat egg; brush top of loaf with egg.
Sprinkle sesame seed on the top.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: three coconut pies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Centers should be soft when you take them out.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, Bundt pan or 3 round cake pans for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: lynn's lazy potatoes
directions: Butter casserole and add half of the potatoes, onion and cheese; salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat as preceding and dot top of casserole with pats of butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: new england cornbread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. For moister stuffing you may need to add more broth. Place stuffing in a casserole that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable oil.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: coconut bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine coconut and milk.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves into a large bowl.
Stir in sugar.

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon in heavy skillet. Add onion. Cook until transparent. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat 45 minutes until lentils are done. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices; set aside. In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Gradually beat in sugar until it's thick.
Gradually stir in oil.
Add flour mix and other ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake(chocolate chip cookies made quick and simple)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: onion fried rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble, leaving bacon grease in pan. Saute onion in grease over medium heat until tender. Add eggs. Scramble until done.
Add rice, bacon, water chestnuts, mushrooms and chopped meat.
Sprinkle in soy sauce to taste and stir over low heat until thoroughly mixed and warm.

title: lemon lime sky high pie
directions: In top of doubler boiler or glass bowl if cooked in microwave oven, combine sugar, gelatin, salt, egg yolks, water, lemon and lime juice, grated lemon and lime peel.
Cook and stir often until thickened.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture resembles unbeaten egg white.
In large bowl, combine 5 egg whites and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until foamy; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Continue beating until peaks are stiff and shiny.
Pour gelatin mixture on meringue; fold gently until combined.
Pour mixture into 10-inch baked pastry shell and chill several hours. Garnish with lemon or lime slices and swirls of whipped cream.

title: delicious potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips or bread crumbs on top.
Bake one hour at 375°.

title: mixed vegetables mornay
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package until just tender. Melt 3 tablespoons butter, blending in flour (do not brown).

Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add seasonings and cheese, stirring just until cheese is melted. Place drained vegetables in a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
Toss bread in remaining butter and scatter on top.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mystery salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Reserve juices of both.
Mix bananas and marshmallows with half cup juices.
Mix rest of juice with pudding mix.
Pour over the fruit.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: three-fruit punch
directions: *Can substitute 1 can frozen lemonade and 1 can frozen lime juice and half sugar amount.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers fine.
Cut up cherries and pineapple. Break up nuts.
In a very large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Then pack in the graham cracker box.
Refrigerate.

title: white trash
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt almond bark and pour over and mix well.
Pour on wax paper and spread out.
Let harden for 2 hours. Break up and put in tight lid container.

title: granny cake
directions: Beat eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add pineapple.
Mix in next 3 ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy overnight rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, put yeast, honey, milk, butter, eggs and salt; mix well.
Gradually add the flour until dough no longer sticks to the sides of bowl.
Mix or knead about 5 minutes.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Place on lightly floured counter; divide into 3 parts.
Roll each part into a 9-inch circle.
Cut into 6 wedges.
Brush with melted butter.
Roll up into crescents and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter (oleo).
Cook broccoli according to package instructions and drain.
Mix together and add rice, cheese, soups and mushrooms.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, 4 minutes. Cool completely. Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Add flour, alternating with date mixture. Mix well. Bake in greased and floured tins at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: kim's egg souffl{2e
directions: Saute
onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Place 1/2 of bread
on
bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 bacon, onions and cheese on bread.
Repeat.

title: grigelhupfe(nutcake)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar slowly; beat until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Mix in crushed nuts.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter and nut mixture, stirring in gently and thoroughly.
Set mixture aside momentarily. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in thoroughly with mixture set aside.
Spoon into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: aunt ginny's frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Stir thoroughly, then fold in Cool Whip. Put in a 9 x 9-inch or 12 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish and freeze overnight.
Take out and cut in squares when needed.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add gelatin, allow to cool. Add bananas and nuts, pour into pie shells and top with Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: camp breakfast
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch rounds or bite size pieces.
Brown in large skillet (frypan).
Dice onion and green pepper.
Add to skillet and cook until tender.
Cut potato and carrot into bite size pieces and add to skillet.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste, if desired.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add spinach, mixing well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and cook slowly until thickened.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, melted oleo, cheese and onion.
Add frozen hash browns.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours until golden brown.

title: fireside snack
directions: Grind all ingredients in food grinder and mix together.
Scoop out the center of the hot dog roll and fill with mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes in oven on cookie sheet.
Serve hot.
Can make ahead and freeze.

title: frozen orange dessert
directions: Mix orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Whip ice cream and add powdered sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Put orange mixture in a refrigerator tray.
Pack ice cream on top and freeze.
Garnish with mint leaves and sugar coated grapes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello.
Cream mixture until well blended. Blend in other ingredients by hand.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Crush croutons. Cook spinach and drain thoroughly. Saut onion and garlic in butter. Mix all ingredients. Chill. Shape into meatball size balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon sponge custard
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add flour, salt, lemon juice and rind, lightly beaten egg yolks and milk. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fidget pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter a deep 2-quart casserole.
Layer potato slices in bottom of casserole.
Season with salt, pepper, sage and nutmeg.
Continue layering and seasoning ham, onion and apples.
Pour broth over all.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients and mix lightly with wooden spoon. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on foil lined cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes until brown. Cool completely before removing from foil.
Store in airtight container.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to directions on grits box.
Add margarine and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until melted.
Cool slightly.
Mix milk and eggs; add to grits.
Add bacon.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's blueberry sour cream pie
directions: Fold egg, brown sugar, flour and vanilla into sour cream. Place half of mixture in pie shell.
Spread on blueberries. Place rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Cool; refrigerate before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
In double boiler, melt cheese, milk and butter with salt and pepper added.
Cool cheese mixture slightly.
Add eggs to mixture and stir in.
Pour over drained macaroni in ovenproof casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Peel stalks of broccoli.
Chop broccoli and other ingredients. Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly, cover and refrigerate.
Mix thoroughly next 3 days.
On fourth day, shape into 4 rolls.
Wet hands first.
Spray broiler pan with Pam or grease with shortening.
Place rolls on pan and bake at 150° for 9 hours.
Turn after 4 hours.
Wrap in foil after they cool.
Keep refrigerated or also may be frozen. Ground venison can be used in place of hamburger.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots for 1/2 hour; drain.
Chop or grind.
Beat egg until light.
Add sugar; mix well.
Stir in butter.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture, alternating with juice and water.
Add nuts and apricots; mix well.
Bake in 1 loaf pan or 2 small pans at 350°.

title: special k casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered; 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Stir together.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Step 1: Mix apples, sugar and walnuts together and let sit 1 hour, stirring often.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse until cool. Add vegetables and eggs. Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and salt together. Toss with spaghetti mixture.

title: sugar coated nutmeats
directions: In saucepan, cook water and sugar until syrup spins a thread. Remove from fire and add vanilla and nutmeats.
Stir until they are well coated; spread on waxed paper being sure the nutmeats are separated.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend sifted flour and salt; stir in.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; sift flour, baking powder and spices.
Dissolve soda in soup and add to first mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Lastly, add nuts and raisins.

title: persimmon drops
directions: Mix together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Blend eggs, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add onion and saltines to mixture.
Mix and pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Add crumbled crackers to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey, celery, grape-nut salad
directions: Add lemon juice and orange rind to mayonnaise.
Mix turkey and other ingredients into mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Makes 4 servings.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Boil together the vinegar, water, sugar, salt and mustard seed.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage.
Mix well. Cool. This will keep several weeks in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: french onion soup
directions: Over medium low heat saute onion in butter until lightly browned.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water and add to onions. Add Worcestershire and dashes of the seasonings to taste and simmer about 20 minutes.
Toast muffins and place one half in bottom of each of four ovenproof soup crocks.
Divide soup between them. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Top each with 2 slices of Mozzarella and run under broiler until cheese is soft and bubbly (5 to 10 minutes).

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones and flake.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, but not hot, cover with smooth peanut butter.
Chill.
Frost with bought chocolate icing.

title: zucchini parmesan casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in salad oil until meat is brown and crumbly.
Add Ro-Tel, tomato sauce, tomato paste and green pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in Cheddar cheese, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add zucchini.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Put into an ungreased shallow 3-quart casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bacon wrapped scallops with hollandaise sauce
directions: Wash and pat dry scallops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each scallop and place in shallow oven-proof pan.
Broil under high heat until browned, turn scallops and brown other side.
Remove from broiler, let drain on paper towels for a minute or two, place scallops on serving platter, drizzle with Hollandaise sauce and sprinkle with paprika.
Very rich, but very nice to serve to very nice people.

title: guacamole
directions: In food processor, chop the onion, chilies and salt together to a smooth paste.
Cut avocado in half; remove seed and scoop out flesh.
Mash flesh with chili paste.
Add tomato, onion and cilantro to avocado mixture and combine well.
Serve immediately. If made ahead of time, dribble with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and layer with vanilla wafers.

title: hamburg soup
directions: In a large saucepan brown meat, then drain the fat.
Add onion and cook until tender (5 minutes).
Stir in all ingredients except the tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, then add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: island fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in heavy skillet; break into pieces.
Add onions, rice and meat; stir until all are hot.
Add egg(s) and mix.

title: best vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add next 4 ingredients, milk last, up to line.
Pour into ice cream freezer and follow its directions.

title: rye bread with dill dip
directions: Mix
sour
cream,
mayonnaise,
onion, parsley and dill weed. Chill.
Cut out round top on bread.
Pull out chunks of bread from inside
to hollow out loaf.
Fill hollow with dip. Use chunks to dip into dill dip.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix flour, salt, paprika, dry mustard and cayenne pepper in a bowl.
Melt butter in skillet and cook onion until soft.
Add flour mixture to onion.
Lower heat and cook for 2 minutes. This will be like a paste.
Add milk.
Stir constantly and bring to a boil.
Mix egg and corn in a bowl. Add to skillet and stir.
Pour mix into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes, browning bread crumbs.
Serves 6.

title: mother's pork tenderloin with rice
directions: Coat each slice of tenderloin with mustard, then coat lightly with flour.
Brown in oil.
Put in ovenproof pan large enough for each piece to lay flat.
Pour can of chicken and rice soup over meat.
Cover with foil and cook in oven at 250° to 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
More rice may be added (approximately 1/2 cup).

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, spread butter on top of cake, then sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: teddy pops
directions: On foil-lined baking sheet, arrange 6 Teddy Grahams in a circle.
Repeat to make a total of 5 circles.
Crush 2 roll candies for each pop.
Arrange crushed bits in an even layer in center of circles, covering surface.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until candy melts and begins to bubble.
Cool.
Peel pops from foil sheet.
Repeat procedure using remaining Teddy Grahams and candies to make 6 additional pops.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate lovers cheesecake
directions: For Crust: In a bowl, combine chocolate wafer crumbs and melted butter. Press crumb mixture firmly on bottom and 1 3/4-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: apple salad
directions: Toss together first 6 ingredients.
Divide mixture and place about 1/2 cup portions on lettuce leaves.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind apples, peppers and onions in food chopper.
Combine with all other ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cube chicken breast; brown onion and chicken in 2 teaspoons oil.
When brown, remove from skillet.
Add flour and water to make a gravy.
Peel and cube potatoes; slice carrots.
Add all to gravy.
Put in casserole and bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, add peas.
Serves about 4.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Pour soup into frying pan on low heat.
As soup warms up, add the cut up mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes after soup has warmed up. Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: blonde brownies
directions: To sifted flour, add baking powder, soda and salt. Add nuts. Melt shortening in saucepan.

Remove from heat and mix in sugar. Cool. Stir in egg and vanilla. Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chips over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool in pan.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in a large pot.
Pour off grease. Add beans, tomatoes and juice.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste with chili powder.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain. Mix beans, catsup, mustard, sauce and sugar in a 9 x 13-inch dish or baking pan.
Add ground beef and stir well.
Garnish top with strips of bacon and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat well and add oil and pumpkin alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool and spread with topping.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices, then cut strips about 2 inches long.
Heat corn oil in skillet over medium heat.
Put garlic clove in hot oil.
Remove after 3 minutes. Add meat to oil; cook over medium heat, turning as needed, until browned.
Mix in onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with stock and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until liquid is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: 1-2-3-4 basic cake mix
directions: Separate eggs; save whites.
Mix egg yolks and all other ingredients on medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cake mix.
Grease and lightly flour 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center of cake is clean.
Cool completely.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: chicken fried steaks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: crab meat bacon rolls
directions: Mix tomato juice and egg.
Add crab, bread crumbs, parsley, lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire and pepper and mix thoroughly. Roll into 18 fingers, about 2 inches long.

title: chicken sauce picante
directions: Place 1/2 stick margarine in skillet; melt, then add chicken, cover and cook until well done.
Then remove lid and add celery, onion and bell pepper.
Replace lid.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Then remove lid and add tomato sauce and cook 20 minutes over low heat. Serve over rice.
Delicious!!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with pudding.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
In a bowl, mix crushed graham crackers, melted butter and brown sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Make a sauce by combining butter, flour and mustard in a saucepan; add milk, stir and cook until thick. Add to other ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: buffalo stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, saute garlic, meat and onion in canola oil. Add mushrooms, including juice; simmer 10 minutes.
Add olives; simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato soup, stir and heat through.
Add sour cream; stir and heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Accompany with cold borscht, tossed green salad and garlic bread.
Serves 4.
Total preparation time: 45 minutes.

title: impossible sausage pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Brown sausage and cook onions with sausage.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender for 15 seconds on high speed. Pour mixture into pie plate. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Refrigerate remaining pie.

title: fried rice with shrimp
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine beaten eggs, soy sauce, dry sherry and pepper; set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat; add cooking oil.
Stir-fry garlic and ginger root in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add chopped onion; stir-fry about 1 minute or until crisp-tender.
Stir in cooked rice, shrimp and peas.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 6 to 8 minutes.
While stirring constantly, drizzle egg mixture over rice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked apples(i use granny smith apples)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Core apples; remove 1-inch strip of skin around upper half to prevent skin from splitting.
Place apples upright in baking dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage the sugar, cream, salt, milk and corn syrup.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°).
Do not stir. Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it loses its gloss.

title: meat stuffing
directions: Saute onions and poultry livers in butter.
Add to meat and other ingredients.
Add milk to moisten, if desired.
Stuff poultry and bake.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Measure 1/3 cup mix in a teacup and add boiling water.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together oleo, 2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add together sour cream, vanilla and salt.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour in 1/2 of batter; top with 1/2 of mixture of pecans, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar. Put other 1/2 of batter in pan and top with remaining half of pecan mixture.
Press in.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
You can double pecans, cinnamon and sugar for a richer cake.

title: diabetic peach pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to peaches.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Roll, fit and seal top. Bake on lower shelf.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour in baking dish or pan and top with bacon pieces.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, 1 stick margarine and confectioners sugar.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Place bananas, pineapple and strawberries in layers on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherry halves and chopped nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: ritzies
directions: Combine above ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Spread on Ritz crackers and place on a cookie sheet.
A table knife works best for spreading about 1 teaspoon on each cracker.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool and top with icing.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cover and cook onions in margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Add beef consomme and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Place 1/2 slice toasted bread in each of four soup bowls and pour hot soup over toast and sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings (about one cup each).

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese and add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in 1 carton Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm. Regular cottage cheese and jello can be used in place of low-fat and NutraSweet.

title: chocolate chip coconut bars
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar until smooth.
Stir in flour, salt, baking soda, vanilla and coconut.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut in 18 bars.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix taco seasoning with ground beef, adding water according to package.
In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream and chilies. Add 1/2 of this mixture to the beef mixture.
Place beef and cheese on tortilla, saving 1/2 the cheese.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour leftover mixture over top.
Cover with leftover cheese.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 400°.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Combine Hidden Valley Ranch dry mix with oil; add remaining ingredients and mix to coat the crackers.
Spread on a cookie sheet and bake in a warm 200° to 225° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk; set aside. Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese together until creamy. In large bowl, add cream cheese mixture, pudding and Cool Whip; mix well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, oil, vinegar, sugar and dressing together and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: pineapple spice cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes a large cake.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Combine the dry instant pudding and the can of pineapple with its juice and mix well.
Fold in the marshmallows and Cool Whip. Chill.

title: buster bar
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and pat into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spoon softened vanilla ice cream over Oreo crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup and caramel sauce over ice cream.
(You do not have to have a solid layer; just drizzle as you like.)
Spoon softened Cool Whip over sauces.
Freeze for at least 3 hours.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Sift flour and mix with sugar. Stir in milk. Pour batter onto melted butter; do not stir. Spoon fruit and juice onto batter. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Spread top with butter and sprinkle with sugar.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Using canned fruit, allow a slice of pineapple, a peach half and an apricot half per person.
Arrange in single layer on large baking sheet, sprinkle lightly with brown sugar and rum and dot with butter.
Put under broiler until fruit is a delicate gold. Serve as a garnish for roast fowl or game, or on a separate platter.
The fruit may be arranged around the fowl or game either in separate pieces or in stacks with pineapple on the bottom, then the peach half, then the apricot half, any way that looks attractive.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine.
Put enough in a 9 x 13-inch pan to coat it. Mix all ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil at moderate-high in wok.
Saute garlic until browned. Add rice.
Mix.
Add soy sauce, peas, carrots, bean sprouts, eggs and ham.
Mix well until heated through.
Season with salt, if desired.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, remove.
Top with chow mein noodles or grated cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onion rings.
Put in a large buttered dish.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer the zucchini and then potatoes.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder, then add another layer of squash.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over top of the ingredients. Top with the shredded cheese. Bake for 1
hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: stromboli
directions: All ingredients are optional according to your taste.

title: chocolate swirl cake
directions: Place ice cream on serving plate.
Arrange cookies around ice cream.
Top with curls.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool at room temperature. Bring water, 2 teaspoons salt and oil to boil.
Add acini de pepe #44.
Cook at rolling boil until acini de pepe #44 is done (about 10 minutes).
Drain; rinse with water; drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Salad may be refrigerated for as long as a week.
Makes 25 servings.

title: chocolate butter brickle bars
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
With a wooden spoon, poke holes in top. Spread caramel ice cream topping on top.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes or more.
Spread Cool Whip over topping and sprinkle with butter brickle bits.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Good and Easy!

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Whisk together and add flour, whole wheat flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool at least 5 minutes on pan.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Follow directions for brownie mix.
Pour into a pizza pan. Takes approximately 10 minutes.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar. Smear onto cooled brownie.
Put drained pineapple on top of cream cheese.
Place bananas around brownie.
Top with any other kind of fruit (your choice).
Melt chocolate chips and butter; drizzle over the "pizza." Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In mixing bowl, pour water over oatmeal and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add sugars and butter and mix well until butter is melted.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and gradually add to the oatmeal mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in 1/2 package of chips.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of boiling water.
Add all ingredients, then chill!

title: dilled mashed potatoes
directions: In large pot, boil potatoes in water with 1 teaspoon salt. Cook until fork easily pierces potato cube.
Remove from heat; drain off water.
Mash potatoes by hand or with portable mixer until free of lumps.
Cut in cream cheese and continue to mix until cheese is blended into potatoes.
Sprinkle potatoes with dill weed and mix in with wooden spoon.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix together all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Layer in baking dish starting with meat mixture, then chips, ending with meat mixture on top.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin puffs(cookies)
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is gone.
In a bowl, mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Cream well.
Add vanilla, soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add raisins; stir.
Form dough into walnut sized balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday soup
directions: Combine Winter Blend vegetables with water; cook until tender. Melt in large pan margarine; add celery, onion and cook a little. Add flour and stir.
Add bouillon cubes.
Add milk and stir.
Add ham, pepper, both salts and then cooked vegetables.

title: spicy hot-dog bites
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hot dogs, according to taste. Pour in crock-pot and simmer.
When sauce gets hot, add hot dogs, cut in bite size pieces.
Cook on low heat approximately 2 hours. Serve from crock-pot.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and oleo.
Add egg.
Add molasses. Alternate flour, cream of tartar and sour milk.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll and form crust on pizza pan with crescent rolls.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Add sausage, cheese and hash browns on top of crust.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and toss all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken biserk
directions: Heat oil in frypan over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown well.
As chicken browns, place sour cream, milk, salt, pepper, flour, garlic and seeded peppers in blender and blend until smooth.
When chicken is browned, transfer to a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Add onions to frypan and cook until limp.
Spoon onions and canned chilies over chicken, then pour sour cream mixture over chicken.

title: cherry cream salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: mixed fruit punch
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in order listed, diluting orange juice with amount of water called for on can.
Add ice cubes, sherbet and ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 40 servings.

title: chili-texas style(makes one gallon)
directions: Using a large stew pot, brown meat in a small amount of oil, stirring until meat has crumbled and not red in color.
Add onions and garlic; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except for flour and water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring frequently to avoid scorching.
Mix flour and water.
Add to chili; stir well.
Continue to cook for 20 minutes.
Cool. Store in refrigerator overnight.
It is better the next day.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in top of double boiler. Add 2 cups water.
Combine egg yolks with lemon juice and beat. Add to sugar mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon extract and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly, pour into pie shell and let cool. Cover with Never Fail Meringue.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Put water and lye in enamel kettle.
Stir, then add corn.
Cook until water is brown and thick.
Remove from heat.
Pour in a drainpan in sink.
Run water over it for several minutes, then put in pan and wash a lot.
Put corn in a big plastic container; cover with water.
Let set all night.
Wash well.
Start cooking and cook until done.

title: dried fruit cake
directions: Boil the first eight ingredients for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
To this mixture, add nuts, flour and soda; mix.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) for about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: yum-yum lime salad
directions: Pour water into large mixing bowl.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise.
Chill until partially set.
Then add cherries, pineapple, milk, cottage cheese and nuts.
Mix with a spoon.
Refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Line unpricked pie shell with a double thickness of heavy duty foil. Bake at 450 degree for 8 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 5 minutes longer. Remove from oven and set aside. Separate one egg, set white aside. In a mixing bowl, beat the yolk and remaining eggs, just until combined. Blend in sugar, salt, and vanilla. Stir in milk. Beat reserved egg white until stiff peaks form. Fold into egg mixture. Carefully pour into crust. Cover edges of pie with foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Remove foil. Bake 15-20 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk and juice, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and rind.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Using a small saucepan, bring milk almost to a boil.
When skim forms on top of milk, remove from heat.
Add shortening, sugar and salt and then pour in cold water.
Use a mixing bowl.
Pour in milk solution.
Add egg and yeast.
Beat until yeast dissolves.
Sift in 2 cups of flour (gradually).
Mix well.
Knead in remaining flour. Roll out dough and cut in biscuit form.
Can be folded over with butter (optional) or leave as is.
To use right away, place on lightly greased cookie sheet and cover with a damp cloth.
Let rise for 1 hour at room temperature.
Cook at 350°.

title: oven stew
directions: Place all ingredients (except potatoes) in well covered 5-quart casserole or Dutch oven.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Pare 1 cucumber.
Score cucumber by pulling the tines of a fork lengthwise through the cucumber.
Cut into very thin slices. Put in a shallow bowl.

title: egg bread
directions: Beat eggs well; mix shortening, baking powder and salt.
Put in meal.
Put in milk (if not thin enough, add water).
Pour in an iron skillet, greased well.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Heat flour, margarine and whipping cream until thick. Pour over Shoepeg corn and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough water to mix well.
Roll out thin.
This will make 3 or 4 pie crusts.
You can freeze these crusts.

title: tater tot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat and spread in bottom of casserole pan, 8 x 8-inch.
Add soup and top with cheese.
Add corn and top with Tater Tots.
Bake in uncovered dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese slices last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: easy cheese biscuits
directions: Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Drop by tablespoon fulls 2 inches apart onto a large greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: holiday bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. In another bowl, combine eggs, sugar, and vegetable oil; beat well. Stir in dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in carrots, pineapple, vanilla and walnuts. Pour into 2 greased, floured loaf pans. Bake for 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tortilla wagon wheels
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread over tortillas.
Roll up; wrap tightly with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unwrap; slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with your favorite salsa.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling in bottom
of pan.
Cover with pineapple (with juice).
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Level, then pour 2 sticks melted oleo over this. Have
coconut and pecans ready to spread on top of oleo.
Bake
40 to
minutes in a 325° oven or until light brown.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, boil potatoes and onions in water until tender, about 20 minutes over medium heat.
Add mixed vegetables, tomato sauce and spices; cook about 10 minutes longer.
Add macaroni.
Turn off heat and cover pan.
Let sit for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with corn bread or crackers.

title: magical pineapple dip
directions: Take a medium-sized bowl.
Take cream cheese, mix it until creamy.
Add pineapple.
Add half can of whipped cream or as much as you like, then add marshmallow cream.
Last, stir all your ingredients together.
Makes a great dip for crackers or other fruits.

title: diet onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Use with crisp bite-size celery, radishes, cauliflower or etc.

title: grasshopper cheesecake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, 1 tablespoon sugar and butter in a bowl. Press into bottom and up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Blend cream cheese in a bowl with 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in liqueurs.
Pour into crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Melt chocolate in saucepan; cool 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Spread over slightly cooled cheesecake.
Refrigerate until set.
Remove from pan; slice and serve.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Cut the onion and celery into rough quarters.
Place them in a food processor, pulsing the machine on and off.
Process until coarsely chopped.
Add the tuna and process briefly to break it up.
Add the egg, bread, butter, mustard, cayenne and black pepper.
Process until blended.
Place flour in a shallow bowl. Lightly flour hands and shape tuna mixture into 4 patties.
Dredge patties lightly in flour.
Cook in skillet.
Serve hot.

title: orange cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot cake
directions: This cake recipe calls for half high-gluten flour and half apple fiber.
You can turn virtually any cake recipe into a source of soluble fiber simply by replacing half the flour with the apple fiber.
Spoon a bit of apricot preserves over the cake as a topping.

title: lazy man's taco
directions: Brown beef, green peppers, onions and celery. Add all the rest and mix well. Put in a casserole dish (covered). Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. You may use a crock-pot for this dish and cook, covered, on medium heat for 3 hours. Serve over corn chips with shredded cheese and lettuce.

title: homemade muesli
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Serve with milk.

title: old-fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: lime mold
directions: Mix lime Jell-O according to package directions.
Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Mix until Jell-O is dissolved.
Refrigerate 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool and chill.
Top with fruit, if desired.

title: mini banana bread loaf
directions: Beat shortening until creamy and glossy or 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add eggs and beat until thick and pale lemon in color.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with bananas.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.
Grease bottom only of 4 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put batter in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until tester inserted comes out clean and dry.
Let bread cool in pans for 10 to 20 minutes, turning onto racks to cool completely.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over cake mix. Top with pats of margarine.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well. At medium-high heat, spray pan with nonstick spray, drop the mixture by heaping tablespoons.
Cook until looks done around edges.
Turn once and cook other side.

title: sand tarts
directions: Chill dough.
Roll out thick (3/8 inch).
Cut with 2 1/2 inch round cutter or use shaped cutter if desired.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wax paper, turning after about 3 minutes (to keep bottom from getting moist).
When finished with all, place in cookie jar.
Mix pieces of fresh bread, torn 1/4 inch.
This will soften and keep cookies moist.
Will need to replace with fresh bread every 2 to 3 days. Feed old bread to birds or use as bread crumbs in other recipes.

title: dunn's ambrosia salad
directions: Mix pudding mix,
milk and Cool Whip together.
Fold the rest of the ingredients in and then chill.
Takes only 5 minutes to make.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil water and sugar together without stirring until it spins a thread when tested. Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg white. Beat until it holds its shape when dropped from the spoon. Add flavoring and spread on the cake. Add the melted chocolate to cooked mixture before adding to the egg white.

title: crab melt aways
directions: Rinse crab meat in colander with cold water and drain on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients together, except English muffins, and spread on English muffins.
Cut into quarters and arrange on cookie sheet.
Freeze at least 30 minutes (may be kept in freezer for weeks).

title: blinchiki(cheese)
directions: Prepare filling by adding sugar, egg and vanilla to cheese and blend thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: one bowl coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients except coconut with mixer.
Add coconut and pour into 2 (9-inch) greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: citrus tea
directions: Cook tea in 1 quart of water. Combine citrus juices and tea plus enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Blend in remaining ingredients, except almonds and paprika.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: crispy fried mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and trim stems slightly; set aside.
Mix flour, salt, mustard, paprika and pepper in a large plastic bag; set aside.
Place buttermilk in a small bowl.
Dip a few mushrooms in bowl.
Place in bag with flour mixture.
Shake to coat.
Heat 2 to 3 inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or heavy saucepan to 375°.
Fry a few mushrooms at a time for 2 to 3 minutes or until deep golden brown, turning several times.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In heavy saucepan, heat milk over low until hot (not boiling). Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved.
Gradually stir in a quarter of the hot mixture into eggs, mixing constantly.
Return all to the saucepan, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir for 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture coats the back of a metal spoon.
Remove from heat (cool).
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.
In a large bowl, combine the cream, fruit and vanilla.
Add the chilled milk mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a chilled freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: eggplant parmesan(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip eggplant slices in egg white and roll in corn flakes.
Brown lightly in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Place eggplant in large casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Gently pour tomatoes over entire casserole. Sprinkle onions over top and season with garlic powder and black pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Recipe makes 6 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade croutons
directions: Toast.
Sprinkle with garlic salt or powder, paprika, pepper and any favorite herb.
Cube the seasoned toast.
Toss into a screwtop jar.

title: cranberry velvet
directions: Press vanilla wafer crumbs and melted butter into pie pan. Bake at 350° and chill.
Whip cheese until fluffy.
Whip cream and vanilla until thick and add cheese.
Add almost a whole can of whole cranberry sauce.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Garnish with rest of cranberry sauce.
Set out to soften before serving.
Serve like pie.

title: banana cupcakes, cream filled
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Cream Cheese Filling and set aside.

title: spanish string beans
directions: In saucepan, cook beans, covered, in small amount of boiling water with salt, until tender, 15 to 20 minutes; drain.

title: corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: orange meringue pie
directions: Line an 8-inch pie pan with the dough.
Pick the dough all over and bake for 18 minutes until light brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Beat cream cheese, salad dressing and Ranch dressing until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust. Mix vegetables together; sprinkle on top of dressing.
Add grated carrots and grated cheese over all.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole dish, cover bottom with Club crackers. Drain can of asparagus and put on top of crumbled crackers. Meanwhile, boil eggs.
Slice and place on top of asparagus.
In saucepan, put cream of mushroom soup, evaporated milk, margarine and Velveeta cheese and melt over low heat.
Pour this over asparagus and eggs, then sprinkle top with crumbled crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red and white cherry freeze
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in pineapple.
Add marshmallows and cherries.
Fold in cream.
Pile into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish or refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm.
Cut in squares and top with whipped cream and cherries.
(For salad, serve plain or with mayonnaise.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice and pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Prepare and refrigerate overnight.

title: bloomin onion(from tampa tribune)
directions: Select a well rounded onion.
Peel outer skin off.
Leave root intact.
Cut off any hanging roots.
Using small sharp knife, divide onion into four sections by making 2 cuts crosswise, beginning at the top and cut toward the root, stop 1/2-inch from root.
Cut each section twice.
Place onion in a bowl of boiling water to cover it and leave 5 minutes.
This will open the onion up.
Soon as they open, put in ice water.
This helps with the opening.
Drain well, drain upside down.
Put flour in paper bag, add onion in beaten egg to cover.
Put cracker crumbs or coating in paper bag. Add onion and shake gently to coat.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before deep frying to a golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Cooked onion may be kept for a time in warm oven.
Use favorite dip.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown turkey; drain.
Mix with taco seasoning and salsa.
Put on bottom of baking dish.
Layer in order on top of meat the beans, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, stirring until beef is crumbly; drain.
Add cheese, soup, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, raisins and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake 65 to 75 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line a baking dish with chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast in a piece of bacon.
Blend sour cream, soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Do not add salt.
Cook, uncovered, about 2 1/2 hours in a 300° oven, until tender or covered at 350° until tender.
Bake, uncovered, for last 10 minutes to crisp slightly.

title: sausage & bean chowder
directions: Mix all together, simmer until done. Serve hot.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until thickened. Fill pie shell; set aside and prepare meringue.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Brown chicken, skin side down, in 3-quart pan about 5 minutes. Remove chicken.
Reduce heat to low.
Add shallots and stir 1 or 2 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Cool. Discard bones and skin.
Dice chicken and return to pan.
Just before serving, return soup to a boil.
Add noodles and cook for required time (about 8 minutes).
Yields about 6 1/2 cups.

title: beef and veggie casserole
directions: Mix all in bowl except Tater Tots.
Put in casserole.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients, form into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and chopped onion.
Drain and set aside to cool.
Stir in pizza sauce, 2 cups cheese and parsley. Blend well.
Arrange buns.
Split and spoon 2 tablespoons mixture on each half and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon remaining cheese.
Heat well and serve.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Lay chicken breast out flat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, garlic salt and parsley.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter each. Roll up tightly.
Roll in flour.
Dip in egg, undiluted with water. Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake until done at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Rolls may be frozen for future use.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on cake box in 10 x 13-inch pan. Mix sour cream and sugar together until smooth; pour on top of warm cake (after it is taken out of oven).
Sprinkle fresh coconut on top of sour cream mixture.
Cake is better if cooked a day before it is cut.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Saute bacon; set aside.
Cook garlic, onions and tomatoes. Make a paste of flour and milk.
Add to pan.
Add cheese; cook slowly until melted.
Stir often.
Add chilies, bacon, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer at least one hour.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Serves 8 to 10.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well. Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour in well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Combine broccoli, soup and rice.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave and pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Melt chocolate in boiling water; add to creamed mixture.
