Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup milk.
Alternately add flour and milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 oiled cake pans.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kathi's quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring shallots and wine to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Sprinkle eggs with salt and pepper; beat lightly.
Beat in cream, nutmeg, wine and shallots.

title: german potato salad
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon margarine. Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and dash of black pepper. Cook until smooth. Remove from heat and stir in water and vinegar. Stir in cooked potatoes. Boil 1 minute. Add bacon and stir.

title: butter-pecan cake
directions: Blend all the ingredients with mixer.
Use a Bundt cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with powdered sugar. Add 1/4 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan before pouring in batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Other canned frostings can be substituted, such as buttercream, cream cheese, etc.)

title: cornish hens
directions: Thaw hens, if frozen.
Heat oven to 350°.
Wash hens and pat dry.
Place, breast side up, on rack in open, shallow roasting pan.
Brush with butter.
Do not add water.
Do not cover.
Roast for 1 hour, brushing with butter.

title: italiano calzono
directions: Roll out dough into portions; dab a little margarine on dough. Let cook for 3 minutes.
Apply one layer of ham or cappicola, layer of pepperoni and layer of Provolone cheese.
Add a seasoning, then add Mortadella with Mozzarella on top.
Close dough, adding a dab of oil on top.
Put in oven at 350°.
Let cook 30 to 40 minutes or desired cooking time (ovens vary).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Roll beef in flour, salt and pepper; brown with onions.
Drain.
Stir in mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: karoline's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and sauce is of desired consistency.
More or less milk may be used as desired.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine.
Bake in a 325° oven on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator overnight, slice and bake 10 minutes.

title: polenta pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 9-inch loaf pan; dust with 1/4 cup cornmeal.
Beat butter, lemon zest and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy, 10 minutes.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add extracts, baking soda and sour cream; mix well.
Mix in 1 cup corn meal, flour and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into batter and put in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Unmold cake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and cloves together. Add the remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: turkey-pasta primavera
directions: Mix all of the above and put in buttered, covered casserole. Bake at 350° to 375° until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli pursuant to package directions. Combine first 7 ingredients and stir well. Spread into 10-inch round casserole. Top with thin layer of bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients together by hand. You may substitute fruit juice for the milk. You could also add a tablespoon of wheat germ for an extra healthy snack. After you mix, spoon into muffin cups or pan. Place in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/2-inch thick.
Salt and pepper lightly if desired.
Saute slowly until brown and done. Place in Pyrex baking dish.
Add vermouth to the drippings, after fat is removed, add lemon juice and rind, stirring constantly. Add sour cream.
Cook 1 minute more without boiling.
Pour over chicken and top with Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler until hot and bubbling.
Can be made ahead of time, refrigerated, then warm thoroughly in oven at 350°.
Best if made a day ahead of time, then warmed thoroughly.

title: pumpkin fritters
directions: Beat egg and add to the crushed pumpkin. Combine with all other ingredients, adding flour last. Drop by small spoonfuls into hot vegetable oil and fry. When finished, sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; tear the chicken into small pieces. Put celery and chicken soup into a large pot.
Take empty soup cans and divide the cream into each and fill with water.
Put all the ingredients in the pot and heat.
Use broth from cooked chicken.
Melt butter in the broth. Use 3/4 bag of each stuffing and mix with broth until it is soft.
Cover bottom and sides of pan with stuffing and pour chicken mixture in the pan.
Crumble rest of stuffing over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp tidbits
directions: Combine the cheese, mayonnaise, shrimp, green onions, dill weed and salt in a bowl; mix well.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut into quarters; place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat source for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
May substitute crab meat for shrimp.
Yield: 48 servings.

title: ritz torte
directions: Add granulated sugar, Ritz crackers and pecans together.
Beat egg whites and baking powder together until it stands in peaks. Mix well.
Grease 9-inch pie pan and pour in mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Place muffin pieces on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients well and spread on muffin pieces.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, broil until they puff and are light golden brown.
Freezing is essential!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes, then cut up.
Chop onion and carrot. In separate bowl, put 2 cups mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon juice of pickles and 1 teaspoon mustard; salt and pepper.
Mix well, then add to salad mix.

title: rich sweet potato pie
directions: Blend peeled potatoes and salt in mixer on medium speed to remove potato strings. Add butter, eggs, sugar and milk, blending well.
Add spices, mixing after each.
Add lemon and vanilla and blend well.
Pour into crusts.
Bake in 300° oven until crusty and lightly browned on top.

title: pimiento sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Chill and serve.

title: deep fried chicken
directions: Prepare chicken as you would to fry (better skinned).
Heat oil in deep pan or deep fryer until mixture will float to top when dropped in.
Mix all the ingredients, having mixture thin.
When oil is hot, dip chicken, a piece at a time, into mixture, dropping immediately into oil.
Cook a few pieces at a time, giving room for chicken to puff up.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat for five minutes on high.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until lightly brown all over.
Cake will fall as it cools.

title: old fashioned apple float
directions: Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.	Pour boiling water over the egg whites and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot with sliced apples. Add remaining ingredients on top of apples. Let this sit overnight. The next day, cook on high for 4 or 5 hours. Then cook on low until desired thickness. Put in sterilized containers and freeze until ready to eat.

title: ruth's cucumber salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Let stand for 3-4 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix instant pudding with the milk.
Mix all other ingredients together with pudding.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in a large bowl.

Line the bottom of large container with graham crackers (layer like you would with a banana pudding), 1st, graham crackers, then pour on Cool Whip mixture, then graham crackers, then the rest of the Cool Whip mixture.

title: my sister's hanky pankies
directions: Brown both meats together.
Drain grease.
Add cheese; cook until melted.
Add spices.
Spread thinly on cocktail rye.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add brown sugar, shortening, oatmeal, pineapple juice and crushed pineapple. Spread into greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sunny oat cookies
directions: Stir together peanut butter, honey and salt until well mixed. Add oats and seeds.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes (watch carefully).
Let cool on sheets for 2 minutes; then cool on racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and chop fine
Let cream cheese soften; fold in sour cream and mix well.
Fold in onions and peppers.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs and buttermilk.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Put in a round baking pan.
Make a cross on top of the bread.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie(quick and easy)
directions: Put 1 pie crust in bottom of a casserole dish or large, deep pie plate.
Pierce the crust.
Combine all other ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour this mixture into the pie crust and cover with the second crust.
Crimp the edges together.
Pierce the crust to allow air to escape.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: whisper pie
directions: In saucepan, combine cherry juice, lemonade and gelatin. Let stand 1 minute, stir over medium heat until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 5 minutes). Cool completely. Beat cream cheese and pudding until light and fluffy. Add gelatin mixture. Chill until mixture is partially set, mounding when dropped from spoon. Add 3/4 of the whipped topping and the cherries, pour into crusts. Chill until firm. Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: no sugar blackberry jam
directions: Heat water and dates on stove until dates are tender.
Simmer blackberries in saucepan.
Add dates and dash of cinnamon, then add glaze powder.
Pour into hot jar and seal.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.

title: pizza pot pie
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add turkey sausage; brown 8 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Cool slightly; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Return sausage to skillet. Pour in pizza sauce; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer 5 minutes more.

title: relish
directions: Mix onions, cabbage, tomatoes and peppers. Place in pot and bring to a boil. Add balance of ingredients; boil 3 minutes. Place in jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Make a	sauce
of
butter,
flour, milk and seasonings. Cook 3 minutes
on
low.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese. Place cooked
vegetables	in
greased casserole and pour cream sauce over
all.	Sprinkle with strips of pimento and slivered almonds or paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in casserole dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over the top of pork chops.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and put in the oven on 350° for 45 minutes.

title: four layer peanut delight
directions: Blend flour and butter.
Add peanuts and press evenly in 9 x 12
pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Second layer: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese and add powdered sugar.
Mix well. Blend in 2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over first layer.
Third layer: Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cup milk. Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cup milk. Combine, mix well and spread over second layer. Fourth layer:
Top with rest of Cool Whip, shredded Hershey bar and 1/3 cup chopped peanuts.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes; very soft mix.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Combine with all remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: glorified rice salad(servings:  10)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir hot rice and marshmallows into hot gelatin mixture.
Add juice from can of pineapple.
Chill until mixture has started to thicken.
Stir in pineapple and chopped apple to which lemon juice has been added.
Chill until nearly set and fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Put in large bowl:
sugar, flour and corn meal.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat with mixer until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes in oven at 400°, then turn to 350° until solid.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Wash oranges and cranberries.
Freeze the cranberries.
In the food processor, add some of the quartered oranges (peels and all) and some cranberries (still frozen).
After all is chopped, add sugar to taste.
This needs to set a day or two to enhance the flavor.
(Refrigerate.)
It also freezes well.

title: veal forestier
directions: Cut veal into 2-inch pieces.
Coat with flour.
In skillet on medium heat in margarine, cook meat until light brown (2 minutes). Remove meat.
Add more margarine, mushrooms, vermouth, water, salt and pepper and parsley.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes until mushrooms are tender.
Return meat to skillet.
Heat through. Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: four fruit cooler
directions: Combine water and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add fruit juices and bananas, mixing well.
Chill.

title: venison tacos
directions: Saute ground venison in margarine in large skillet.
When venison is brown, add pepper, onions, lemon juice, soy sauce and mustard; cook five minutes more.
Spoon meat into warm taco shells.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and sour cream if desired.

title: 3 step cake(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, poke holes in top and spread Eagle Brand milk over top. Cool completely. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy bars. Keep in pan you bake in and refrigerate.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and pepper.
Combine noodles.
Add remaining ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Combine with 1 teaspoon salt water; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes; drain.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes; toss with butter.
Combine with eggplant, egg, half of cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover; top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: geraldine's vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in kettle.
Add tomatoes and other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix and mandarin oranges (use oranges instead of water).
Can add 1 carton of
egg substitute to equal 2 eggs, if desired (this is optional).
Mix and bake (follow box instructions and use Pam to grease cake pans).

title: pork roast
directions: Wash roast and place in baking dish.
Salt and pepper the roast (some use red pepper but that is too hot for my family). Place mushrooms, onions and cooking wine around roast, placing figs on top of roast.
Pour fig juice over roast.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 325° for about 3 hours.
Very good!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on package.
Grease a casserole dish and pat in packaged stuffing (save some to sprinkle on top).
Mix squash, soup, sour cream and carrot together.
Spread squash mixture over stuffing.
Dot with butter pats and sprinkle with leftover stuffing.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: peanut butter cutouts
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
In a large bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Beat in both sugars until blended. Beat in egg.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until well mixed. Divide dough in thirds; wrap each portion and refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Roll out dough, 1/3 at a time, on lightly floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
If desired, sprinkle cookies with colored sugars. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lamb with cheese and pasta(serves 4)
directions: Bring a pot of water to boil for the pasta.
Heat a frying pan and saute the garlic in the oil.
Just as the pasta is finishing, add the cooked lamb to the hot garlic oil; saute for just a moment.
Toss the meat with the drained pasta, along with all other ingredients.

title: mother's mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order as listed.
Place on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon drops.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: fajita marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This is an excellent marinade for chicken or beef, to be cooked on the outdoor grill or baked in the oven.
Best results if chicken soaks for 2 to 3 days in marinade covered in the refrigerator.
Or can be used after 1 to 2 hours of soaking.
Meat will be very tender.
Marinade can be re-used if kept in refrigerator.

title: meat pie(makes four 9-inch pies)
directions: Mix meats.
Break up and add spices.
Cover with water.
Cook 1 hour on medium heat.
Drain off fat.
Add 8 mashed potatoes. Bake in crust at 400° for 30 minutes, until crust is browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; combine remaining ingredients except for bread crumbs.
Fold until mixed.
Layer broccoli and sauce in casserole. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top the last 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream sugar until thick.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
In a large skillet, cook and stir onions in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, pimento and jalapeno peppers and gravy from Fri Chick.
In a 4-quart casserole layer 1/2 noodles and 1/2 the soup mixture and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter or margarine and cream cheese.
Mix with confectioners sugar and pour over cake mix, coming to within 1-inch to 1/2-inch of edge.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes and then turn upside down.

title: potato patties
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except margarine.
Mix well.
Shape into patties and coat with additional flour or bread crumbs.
Fry in hot margarine until golden brown, turning once.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add cream of mushroom soup and grated cheeses.
Mix until cheese is melted and add milk and stir. Pour into casserole and arrange Tater Tots in a single layer across the top.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is bubbling, about 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn muffins
directions: Measure flour, meal, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Stir together.
Make a well in the center.
Beat egg in a small bowl until frothy.
Pour into well.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Leave in pan for 5 minutes, then remove.
Serve warm with butter and jam.

title: grannie myrt's apple jelly
directions: Wash and cut into quarters the apples.
(Do not peel or get seeds out.
Cut whole apples.)
Put in boiler.
Cover with water. Boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set in water that they're boiled in overnight.
Next morning, put apples and juice in cloth bag and strain.
Squeeze juice out well.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a large baking dish or large cake baking pan.
Put everything in layers as listed.
Melt oleo and spoon this over all the layers.
Bake around 375° for about an hour.

title: apple taffy dip
directions: Blend well, folding in nuts (black walnuts or pecans).
Dip apple slices or spread taffy onto apple.
Also good as a spread on pumpkin bread.

title: poor man's punch
directions: Mix sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Chill.
When ready, add ginger ale.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Melt oleo and add brown sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or a little longer.

title: king ranch soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Top with corn chips and shredded cheddar.

title: no sugar added pineapple cheesecake pie
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 1/4 cup pineapple for topping.
Beat cream cheese, cool whip and equal until fluffy.
Fold in pineapple and pour into crust and top with remaining pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: fry bread scones
directions: Mix oil, yeast, water and sugar; set aside for 5 minutes.
Mix flour and salt and add to oil mixture.
Knead 6 to 8 times. Insert bowl on top of dough and wait 5 minutes.
Fry in hot oil until golden.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Mix in zucchini. Sift dry ingredients together and add zucchini mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 1 hour or until done at 325°.

title: easy pickles
directions: Drain and slice pickles and put back into jar.
Bring all other ingredients to a boil, stirring to be sure sugar is completely dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Pour over pickles.
Let set overnight or longer.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
Delicious on hamburgs, hot dogs, etc.
Makes kitchen smell nice while preparing.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: In 1 1/2 quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onion.
Bake 5 minutes in the microwave.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 8 minutes on High.

title: vegetable cheese tart
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until blended. Spoon into pie or tart shell. bake in a 375° oven 45 minutes or until knife 1/2 in center comes out clean.

title: vodka slush
directions: Freeze mixture and use 2 to 3 Tbsp. per glass and fill with seven-up.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix thoroughly; can roll, cut and cook immediately, or refrigerate overnight.

title: deluxe cheesy potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with hot water and let stand uncovered 15 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients except corn flakes.
Spread in ungreased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Bake uncovered until golden brown at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly. Mix sugar and shortening. Add eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly after each addition.

title: creamy pimento cheese spread
directions: Heat evaporated milk and cheese in saucepan until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar, pimento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.

title: peach punch
directions: Slice orange into thin slices and set aside.
Pour together in a punch bowl the pineapple juice and peach Schnapps.
Float the orange slices and mint leaves on the top and serve.

title: dillie beans(makes 7 pint jars)
directions: Bring vinegar, water and salt to boil.
Add beans either cut in chunks or whole over dill.
Add 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed, 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper in each jar and fill with boiling brine, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal.
Boil in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Store in cool dry place.
Can be used in cocktails or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: fruit temptation salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine apple juice, yogurt, mayonnaise and sugar, stirring with a whisk until smooth.
Pour over fruit mixture. Toss well. Serve on lettuce lined plates.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Serve on cooked pasta sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Dust chicken with flour in a large skillet; heat oil and butter on medium-high.
Brown chicken; remove chicken and add fresh vegetables to skillet (celery, sliced diagonally; pepper, sliced into strips and onion, chopped).
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet; simmer, covered, for 1 hour until the chicken is tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: danish stew(sailor's stew; skipperlabskovs)
directions: Remove excess fat from meat, cut it in 1 to 2-inch cubes and put in saucepan with water.
Bring to a boil and remove any film which may form.
Add onions and bring to a boil again.
Add bay leaves. Cover with lid and continue cooking over low heat for about 1 hour.
Add cubed potatoes; cook until meat is tender and potatoes have become so soft that they thicken the gravy and have the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour into serving dish; sprinkle with chopped parsley or chives. Top with small plops of butter.
Serve chopped smoked ham separately.
Serve with dark rye or rye bread.

title: joanne's chicken recipe
directions: Mix chicken with mushroom soup and sour cream and add a couple of tablespoons of broth from the cooked chicken.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Crush Ritz crackers in Ziploc bag; add 1/4 stick melted margarine.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Bake the first 6 ingredients in a 10 x 15-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Mix eggs and pineapple.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts by hand. Bake as before.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Use a basic mix, adding 1/2 cup raw, crunchy peanut butter to the batter.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting. This is an ideal cake to serve at a child's party.

title: aunt millie's german butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cream butter; add sugar, small amount at a time, cream after each addition.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla extract, mix well.
Add sifted ingredients; mix well.
Roll dough in balls about 3/4 inch.
Put balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 275° for 50 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil in salted water until tender. Drain.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Heat and pour over potatoes.
Melt oleo and add green onion.
Cook until tender.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour.
Add chopped dates, nuts and flavoring.
Spread in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Place in a lightly buttered 8-inch square baking dish.

Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon and sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Sprinkle mixture evenly over peaches. Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 375° oven or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with cream or milk, if desired. Serves 6.

title: congo bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 335° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 45 squares.

title: easy homemade ice cream
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into ice cream freezer. Fill to the top of your freezer with whole milk.
If you use fresh fruit in this recipe, eliminate the vanilla.

title: clam sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour sauce over cooked and drained pasta.

title: al fresco salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with next 5 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise and seasoning as desired.
Make a day ahead.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Place ribs in skillet; add hot water and cover.
Drain and dry.
Heat skillet; add ribs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over browning ribs.
Turn ribs often. Cook until well browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.

title: lemon cream syllabub
directions: Beat egg and cook with vinegar, sugar and lemon until thick. Cool off.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
Light and fluffy in texture; this makes a pleasing accompaniment to lemon cake or fruit desserts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk.
Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients.
Pour into crusts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients with cooked macaroni.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs or grated cheese and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir salad dressing, lemon juice, peel and dill seed until blended.
Place fish on greased grill or racks of broiler pan. Brush with half of the sauce.
Grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes, turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue grilling or broiling for 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with forks.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix bean dip and salsa mix and put on bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix together.
Put on top of dip and salsa.
Put Cheddar shredded cheese on top of sour cream mixture. Put black, sliced olives on top of everything.
Serve with Fritos or Tostitos.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients into pie plate.
Heat Crisco and water until Crisco is melted.
Add vinegar.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix with fork until well moistened.
Remove a small amount (walnut size).
Press into bottom and sides of dish.
Flute edges.
Prick with fork.
If making more than one, mix completely
separate. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: open-face party sandwiches
directions: Trim bread and cut diagonally.
Spread on bread and broil until it is slightly brown and cheese has melted.
Serve hot and you can't keep these made fast enough.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix juices with sugar.
Dissolve jello in water.
Add milk and cream.
Freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli to boil, separating broccoli with fork.
Stir in Velveeta, reduce heat to low.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients; combine milk and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add pork mixture and bread.
Pour into sprayed 11 x 7 baking dish.
Cover and chill 8 to 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set and brown.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Cut dill pickles into bits.
Cover with ice cubes and soak for one hour.
For ten minutes, boil remaining ingredients together. Pour over the pickles from which the ice cubes have been drained. Put in jars which can be stored in refrigerator.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Whip butter, sugar and egg with fork.
Cook until thick. While hot, add cream cheese, pimientos and pecans.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: pawley's island tuna
directions: Wash and dry tuna.
Remove skin and dark meat (will be considerably darker than the rest of the tuna).
Combine teriyaki and soy sauces in a flat container.
Press in garlic; stir well. Add tuna; coat both sides.
Refrigerate, turning the tuna 2 or 3 times during the marinating time.
(Note:
Marinating can be done as little as 45 minutes prior to grilling, but no more than 3 hours before.)

title: date nut log
directions: In a bowl, combine 2 cups of graham cracker crumbs, marshmallows, dates and walnuts.
Stir in cream; mix thoroughly. Shape into a 1/4-inch x 3-inch log.
Roll in remaining crumbs. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and put into crust.
Start in 400° oven for 15 minutes to set pie, then turn oven to 300° until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook 10 minutes; drain.
Put layer of beans in casserole, then layer of brown sugar, layer of bacon and onion.
Add tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Bake at 325° until beans are done.
Add more water if beans get too dry from time to time.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water to make a paste.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix in mixture.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Put about 2 to 3 inches apart.
Flatten with glass.
When cool, fill with filling.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add milk as needed to make spreading consistency.

title: waldorf salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: Place apples in a large bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice. Add celery, walnuts and grapes.
Blend mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and salt.
Toss with salad ingredients to coat evenly. Chill.
Serve salad in lettuce-lined bowl.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
With a fork dipped in water, make a crisscross on each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix shortening, flour, baking powder and sugar together. Blend well.
Add 1 cup milk, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix about 2 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup milk and egg whites to batter.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into floured pan and cook in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and flour. Gradually beat hot milk into egg mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla until blended. Cover with plastic wrap and cool.
(Filling will keep 2 days in refrigerator.)

title: rouladen
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: creamy chicken and jalapeno nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken, cream cheese, peppers, onion, garlic, cumin, chili powder and grated cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until blended.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: smoked trout
directions: Blend the horseradish and sour cream in a small bowl.
Arrange the smoked trout on a platter with a bowl of this horseradish sauce or on individual salad plates.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Put filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with ice cream (any choice of yours).

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Remove core from cabbage. Separate the leaves and boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until soft enough to roll.
Drain, save liquid.
Combine ground beef, chopped onion, uncooked rice, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Shape and place medium sized patty in center of leaf.
Roll to enclose meat.
Shred remaining cabbage and mix with sauerkraut and sliced onion.
Place 1/2 of the cabbage, sauerkraut mixture in bottom of large pot.
Place rolls on top of mixture.
Place rest of mixture on top of rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over mixture.
If necessary, add water to cover.
Cover and bring to boil over medium heat, then reduce heat and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp on the barbecue
directions: Place shrimp on a wooden skewer stick (use six shrimp per stick).
Salt and pepper shrimp.
Melt butter and garlic.
Dip shrimp into your melted butter and garlic. Put aluminum foil on heated grill top.
Punch small holes in aluminum foil.
Put shrimp on skewer stick on grill.
Brush more butter mixture on shrimp. Cook until shrimp is pink.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, rice, sugar and vanilla to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
About 5 minutes before hour is up, beat eggs in a bowl with mixer.
Add eggs to milk and rice mixture.
Remove from stove. Pour into bowl(s) and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Use on strawberries, peaches, pineapple, etc.

title: simple peach pie
directions: Melt margarine; put in baking dish first.
Mix together milk, sugar and flour; pour on the margarine and stir together.
Place peaches over mixture.
Bake at 300° until brown.
It will make its own crust.

title: red wine sauce
directions: Combine melted butter, tomato sauce, prepared mustard, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and red wine in bowl; mix well.
May use additional can tomato sauce, if desired.

title: fast spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain well.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add drained meat and spaghetti.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: irish slaw
directions: Toss cabbage and onion.
Mix other ingredients together. Combine cabbage mixture and dressing.
Toss together.

title: caramel nut corn
directions: Divide popcorn and nuts between two ungreased pans.
Cook brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and nuts, stirring until corn is well coated.
Bake, uncovered, at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: teaspoon doughnuts
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and spices.
Beat sugar, eggs and salt together until light and fluffy.
Add milk and beat again. Pour into flour mixture and beat for a second or two.

title: better than kissing cake
directions: Make cake mix by instructions on box.
Let cool completely. Boil pineapple and sugar together for 5 minutes and pour over top of cake.
Make pudding by instructions on box and pour over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cut into small pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel and 1/2 package Doritos.
Mix together and pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and rest of Doritos.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: yummy rice pudding
directions: Stir milk and egg into pudding; mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes or serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve warm or cold.
Stir before serving.
Smooth and creamy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all except cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Add remaining batter. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla, soda, salt and flour.
Roll out. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mushroom watercress salad
directions: Refrigerate watercress.
Put mushrooms in a shallow dish. Place salt in small bowl.
Pour vinegar over salt, stir to dissolve.
Add pepper, oil and mustard; mix well.
Pour over mushrooms.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Pour mushrooms and dressing over watercress; toss.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Put hamburg, salt, pepper, bouillon cubes and water to simmer. Add chopped celery, onion and carrot.
Add diced potato.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add beans (drained) and tomatoes, also the barley.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook on low heat.

title: green bean and shoepeg casserole
directions: Drain beans, corn and water chestnuts. Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: dinette cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend on low speed, scraping often for 1 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Great with fresh strawberries.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Chop onion, garlic and pepper into small pieces.
Add olive oil into large saucepan (medium heat).
Lightly brown the onion, garlic and pepper in the olive oil.
Add canned tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Heat on medium until paste is combined with tomatoes and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low.
Let simmer lightly for six hours.
If adding meatballs, do so after 2 hours.

title: original teriyaki marinade
directions: Chill in marinade over night.
Cook 40 min.- 1 hour at 350°. Recipe can be cut in half.

title: cuban rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water with cinnamon and lemon.
When rice is cooked, add the 8 cups of milk, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt and cook about an hour on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all this in a casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. This can also be microwaved for 8 minutes on High, then 12 minutes on Medium.
These times will vary with each microwave. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix sour cream, pizza sauce, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese. Spread on a large serving platter.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Top with pepperoni. Refrigerate until serving time. Serve with Italian bread sticks, cut into cubes.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of pan.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and layer on top of beef.
Put bacon on top of chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken runs clear.
Serve over rice.
Can also be made in crock-pot.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into pieces and set aside.
Mix tomatoes, cheese and broth in a skillet until cheese melts (this makes cheese sauce).
In a casserole dish, layer 1/2 bag Doritos, 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of sauce, then layer other half of ingredients in same order.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Melt butter and add oil.
Stir-fry for a few minutes.
Add the wine.
Cover pot and steam for about 3 minutes.
Stir into mixture the cooked pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
In blender, stir in soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and broth.
Grease casserole dish, layer with chicken, tortillas (cut in bite-size pieces), then cheese, onion and sauce from blender.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together the pineapple, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and chill.

title: hominy
directions: Set up kettle in yard and build a fire around 3 sides (not on the side the wind is from, leave this side to stir from).
Add 4 gallons water and lye in kettle; dissolve lye.
Add corn and bring to a boil.
Slowly cook for about 2 1/2 hours or until husk turns loose.
Add hot water as needed, stirring continuously to keep from sticking.
Set kettle off of fire and put corn in a tub or other container and wash 4 or 5 times.
Clean kettle and put back on fire.
Add 4 gallons of water and corn.
Slowly cook for another 2 hours until tender.
Put corn in big container and wash 3 or 4 times.
Soak in water overnight in enamel container.
Wash 3 or 4 times before freezing or canning.
Makes approximately 20 quarts.

title: gingerbread with caramel sauce
directions: Mix sugar, crisco and egg together.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Thoroughly blend soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, spreading mixture evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and corn flakes (or crackers, crushed) and parsley flakes and top mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and spread on bread.
You can also do this with potted meat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in buttered pan.
Bring other ingredients to boil. Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir while cooling.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Whip Dream Whip with the milk until soft peaks appear.
Cream the cheese, sugar and flavoring and combine with Dream Whip.
Beat well.
Pour into dish and top with cherry topping.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Add sauce.
Layer in a casserole dish the spaghetti, Mozzarella, Provolone, Swiss and pepperoni. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Continue to layer until ingredients are used.
Sprinkle with basil and oregano.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Prepare whipped topping (Dream Whip) and fold into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into shell.
Sprinkle with some of the nuts. Pile on chocolate Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with rest of nuts and a bit of shaved semi-sweet chocolate.
Chill until firm.

title: green chili burritos
directions: Simmer all together.
Add 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Heat flour tortillas.
Fill tortillas.
Put in baking dish.
Top with enchilada sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated and cheese melts.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream(the best)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into freezer can.
Pack ice and salt around can and freeze.

title: bambini appetizers
directions: Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese in a bowl. Preheat oven to 350°.
Halve each biscuit horizontally, forming 20 thin biscuits.
Shape one piece of dough into an oval about 2 1/2 x 4-inches.
Place a slice of pepperoni on dough.
Top with about 1 tablespoon of cheese mixture.
Moisten edges.
Fold the dough over the enclose filling and pinch to seal the edges.
Place onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and repeat with the remaining dough.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti by package directions and drain.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper; stir well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth; stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cream and stir.
Stir in chicken.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook
beef
until crumbly.
Mix rest of ingredients and toss. Add dressing and beef just before serving.

title: winnies wrapped in bacon
directions: Wrap each winnie with strip of bacon.
Secure with toothpick. Put in crock-pot.
Pour in 1 pound box brown sugar.
Cook on medium until sugar melts, then cook on low until bacon is done.
Better if bacon is not crispy, but done.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, flour and walnuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: easy homemade pancakes or waffles
directions: Blend flour, soda and baking powder in a mixing pitcher and add egg and milk.
Blend with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour onto hot greased griddle or waffle iron.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender; cool.
Alternate in layers with carrots, pepper rings and onion slices.
(May chop the onions and peppers when serving to large crowds.)
Beat remaining ingredients well with beater, until completely blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
May be prepared several days before serving and may be served hot or cold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, then beat in sugars.
Add oil slowly; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour (1/2 of it).
Add 1/2 zucchini and alternate.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter; then mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Take can biscuits and roll them in melted butter; then roll the buttered biscuits in the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place them in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until brown around the edges.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in pan.
Mix avocados and lemon juice.
Layer over bean dip.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with 1/2 package taco seasoning. Add to pan.
Add layer of cheese, chopped tomatoes, green onions and olives.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into serving size pieces.
Cook in small amount of water until tender.
Put into casserole dish.
Pour well mixed sour cream and shrimp soup over cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This is easy and very good.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Heat in crock-pot and serve.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Skin and debone chicken breasts.
Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
In a wok or skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Stir-fry mushrooms and onion in butter about 2 minutes or until soft.
Add chicken pieces and stir-fry about 5 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Blend sugar, flour and eggs together.
Mix in melted butter. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into your unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: pat watkins sweepstake divinity
directions: In a medium size heavy pan, combine the first four ingredients.
Cook this mixture over a medium-high heat until reaching 232°.
Remove from the heat and pour 1/3 of the mixture into the beaten egg whites and mix well.
Return the remaining sugar syrup to the heat and bring to 244°.
Pour the mixture into the egg mixture; beat in the vanilla and continue to beat until the mixture loses the gloss.
Spoon the mixture onto waxed paper and shape into rolls.
Roll each roll into the chopped nuts, then chill.
Slice into rounds and serve.

title: adele's fruit soup
directions: Soak fruit and tapioca overnight.
The next day cook all ingredients, except cherries, in 1/2 gallon of water for about 1/4 hour.
(Wine may be substituted for some of the water.)
Add cherries and cool.
Very good for breakfast or an evening snack.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Beat egg yolk and add milk. Add to dry ingredients, beating constantly.
Add butter or oil last of all.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cut in big pieces.
Put in casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover with crackers, then poppy seed.
Drizzle margarine over.
Cover and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add one egg at a time. Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour gradually with milk. Mix with blueberries until damp.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake in tube pan.

title: asparagus with lemon butter and pecans
directions: Place the asparagus in a shallow baking dish that has been greased with some of the butter.
Dot the asparagus with the remaining butter and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Sprinkle on the pecans.
Season with pepper and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, just until the dish is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pasta with cream, basil, bacon
directions: Cook fettucini according to package; drain.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add cream and stir until cream thickens.
Add cheese and basil.
Stir until smooth.
Crumble bacon and add to cheese and cream mixture.
Combine with fettucini and serve immediately.
Great with a salad and Pillsbury corn bread twists.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, put peaches and berries together.
Mix in separate bowl, flour, nutmeg, oats, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over peach mixture; bake 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Cool and serve.

title: zippy zucchini
directions: Toss ingredients and microwave or bake until al dente.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Add butter and remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish bake in 375° oven.
Bake until golden brown.

title: green apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli; place rice in casserole.
Pour melted margarine over and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute the onions and green pepper in a large frying pan. Add ground beef and brown; drain fat.

title: honey-butter peas
directions: Prepare peas according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine honey and margarine in small mixer bowl; beat until fluffy.
Pour over peas.
Serve immediately.

title: trash can food(good for cookouts.)
directions: Purchase an aluminum garbage can.
Layer ingredients in order. Cook over charcoal or campfire.
When carrots on top are tender, it's ready to serve.
Dump can on table covered in aluminum foil. Serve yourself.

title: microwave tuna pie
directions: Mix first 9 items and press into 8-inch pie pan.

title: fruit dessert(or salad)
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge swirl cake
directions: Fold into bundt pan.
Spoon in chocolate ice cream topping (3/4 c.) randomly over top of mixture, then swirl through with butter knife.
Cover with remaining vanilla wafer mixture, cover and freeze for 2 - 3 hours.
Serves at least 10!

title: make ahead mashed potatoes for a crowd
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place in casseroles. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May store in refrigerator for a week.

title: oatmeal griddle cakes
directions: Mix buttermilk and rolled oats in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight, stirring once or twice.
Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Add buttermilk mixture to well beaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add liquid all at one time.
Stir only until blended.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix together. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaf pans.
May add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: filipino mochi
directions: Combine the ingredients in order as listed.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer fruit punch
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, place mixture in a punch bowl and add remaining ingredients.

title: brown bread
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil in covered saucepan.
Set aside to cool.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Alternately add raisins and flour mixture to the liquid.
Mix in nuts.
Oil four 1 pound coffee cans.
Divide batter evenly (1/2 full).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In a mixing bowl stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper. Add beaten eggs.
Stir only until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.

title: cocoa zucchini cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with the zucchini to the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a lightly oiled Bundt pan or bake 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven when a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: tarragon chicken strips
directions: Saute chicken strips in butter and season with spices, except tarragon.
Remove from pan with slotted spoon to heated platter. Deglaze pan with white wine.
Add chicken broth, stir and return chicken to pan to poach for 5 minutes.
Remove chicken, add cream and tarragon and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until sauce is thick.

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub shortening into flour.
Use milk to make a stiff dough (3/4 cup is sufficient).
Shape into dumplings by rolling very thin and cut into strips or drop from spoon into chicken broth.
Place lid on pot and cook 12 to 15 minutes slowly.
Do not stir or remove lid from boiler until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 1/2 or 10-inch spring-form pan and coat lightly with flour. In medium bowl, toss gingersnap crumbs with melted butter until moistened.
Press crumbs into bottom and 1-inch up sides of the prepared pan.
Bake 12 minutes or until crust begins to color.
Let cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all except cracker crumbs; mix well.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Cover with crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbling and brown.

title: fresh corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Put corn in a baking dish with lid.
Add whipping cream.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Grease cookie sheet. Mix baking mix, apple, brown sugar, ginger, milk and egg until dough forms.

Do not overmix. Pour onto surface dusted with baking mix; roll in baking mix to coat. Shape into a ball; knead 10 times. Place dough onto cookie sheet and pat into 8-inch circle. Brush with milk. Sprinkle with sugar. Cut into 8 wedges. Bake 12 to 14 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: chocolate cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each one. Sift cocoa with flour and add slowly to egg mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until your cake tests done. Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: shrimp or crawfish au gratin
directions: Saute vegetables in melted butter until well done, not browned.
Blend flour into mixture, stirring constantly.
Add milk, egg yolks and seasonings.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, until mixture begins to thicken.
Add shrimp, parsley and 1/2 of the cheese.
Blend well and pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake about 20 minutes at 350 degrees, until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir
all ingredients together except 1 cup of stuffing and 3 tablespoons
of
butter
or
margarine to put on top of casserole. Oil
an
8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil
chicken
innards	in water until cooked, cool and chop into small pieces.	In large pot brown meat, onions, bell peppers and garlic until all veggies are tender.
Add chicken innards. Season
to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Add rice and stir well.
Add chopped green onions, stir and enjoy.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place the cinnamon sticks, cloves, allspice and lemon peel in a double thickness of cheesecloth; bring up corners of cloth and tie with kitchen string to form a bag.

title: chocolate cinnamon bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Add butter or margarine, shortening, 1 egg and 1 egg yolk.
Blend well with wooden spoon, or on low speed of electric mixer.
Turn into a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 3/4-inch jello roll pan; spread evenly with spatula.
Beat egg white slightly; brush over mixture.
combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, chocolate pieces and walnuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of pineapple juice in a saucepan.
Spray sides and bottom of a cake pan.
Pour brown sugar mixture into it.
Arrange pineapple rings and cherries on top.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on package, or make your favorite cake recipe and pour over mixture in cake pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand to cool a few minutes, then invert onto a plate.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread; cut in 1/2-inch cubes and set aside. Cut remaining bread in 1-inch cubes; place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasonings. Spoon over bread cubes. Sprinkle remaining unbuttered cubes over chicken mixture. Combine eggs and milk; pour over all. Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 55 minutes. Cool on rack before slicing.

title: ham bake
directions: Prepare dinners as directed.
Add ham and green pepper. Season to taste.
Place in a 10 x 6-inch deep baking dish. Combine milk and eggs; pour over dinner mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 10 to 12 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in blender or rotary beater.

title: bloomfield surprise
directions: Place biscuits on bottom of pan.
Try to cover entire bottom. Bake for a few minutes.
Take out and peel top layer of biscuits off.
Spread layer of beans on bottom layer of biscuits.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix everything together.

title: apple fritters
directions: Add baking powder to flour.
Beat egg.
Add milk, oil, salt, flour mixture and sugar; beat until smooth.
Dash cinnamon on apples, then stir into batter.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil. They turn themselves when browned on one side, or you might need to help.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve with pancake syrup.

title: kids play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a medium pot.
Add water, coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes until the mixture forms a ball in the center of the pot.
Take it out.
Put it on a floured surface and knead until the ball is firm.
Place in airtight bag or container and store in refrigerator.

title: frozen pink salad
directions: Mix all, but Cool Whip, in electric mixer.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Soften 15 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and milk. Add 1/3 cup cheese, bread crumbs and pepper to milk and eggs. Stir in zucchini and onion.
Turn mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 300° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 5 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Dust with graham cracker crumbs.

title: cream cheese mint
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well.
Add coloring and flavoring and mix well again.
Form into small balls.
Dip top of ball in super-fine granulated sugar and press sugared side into commercial mold.
Release onto wax paper and let air dry overnight or you can roll into bite-size balls and dip in chocolate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 1-quart microwavable dish, heat butter until melted. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually stir in milk. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes. Layer 1/2 of the sliced potatoes, onions and sauce in a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers; cover and microwave 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Total microwave time is 25 1/2 to 29 1/2 minutes.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes.
Pan-fry sausage.
Chop potatoes and cut sausage into pieces, except 6 to 8 links, reserved as garnish.
Put 3 tablespoons of sausage drippings into large frying pan.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and brown lightly.
Stir in 2 to 3 cups milk and bring to simmer.
Mix 6 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water and shake well.
Add this to the milk mixture and stir until desired thickness.
Mix in seasonings.
Place a layer of potatoes and sausage in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour some of the gravy over this and continue layers until casserole is filled 1 1/2-inches from the top.
Garnish with whole sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered or uncovered, as you prefer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together thoroughly until creamy and smooth.
Add a little milk, if desired thinner.

title: venison tenderloin
directions: Venison should be soaked in salt water 1 hour or more before using.
Roll venison in flour, salt and pepper and brown in frypan with small amount of oil.
Bring onion soup mixed with 3 cups water to boil for a few minutes.
Place venison in baking dish and pour soup mixture over it.
Bake at 325° until tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: helen's honey whole wheat bread
directions: Note:
Helen puts in 2 1/2 cups with kneading.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Cook and drain broccoli until barely tender. Add beaten egg, soup and cheese. Fold in mayonnaise.
Put in greased 9
x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together brown sugar and butter; add eggs, orange peel and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture; beat after each addition.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While cookies are warm, frost with Orange Icing.

title: chile sans carne(meatless)
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven or heavy soup pot.
Saute onion, garlic and peppers until the onion begins to turn translucent. Add tomatoes, beans and spices and simmer for at least 30 minutes. Serve over steamed rice.

title: dan's mom's carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 360° oven for 55 minutes.
Goes well with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: raspberry-apple vinaigrette
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Yields 1/3 cup.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Add 2 c. raw rhubarb, cut fine. Cover with 1/2 c. brown sugar and nuts. Bake 350°
40 to 50 minutes. Makes a small cake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add salt, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add flour.
Then fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 10-inch iron tube pan (floured pan) for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Place in a cold oven and then turn the oven on and set temperature.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Tip:
You may use caraway seed or cumin in place of herbs, if desired.
Use about 1 1/2 teaspoon for 4 large potatoes.

title: mama's roast beef and vegetables
directions: Use a 4 or 5 pound roast.
Rub in about 1 teaspoon of salt, then sear in a hot skillet until brown on both sides.
Remove to roaster and add a little water.
Put covered roaster in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes, then lower heat to 325°.
Cook for at least 30 minutes, then add potatoes, carrots, onions and 3 stalks of celery according to the amount needed for your family.
Cover and keep at 325° until meat and vegetables are tender (at least 1 hour and 15 minutes).
This slow cooking helps tenderize less choice cuts of meat.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and combine.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Combine and heat broth, cheese, soup, bell pepper, onion and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat 1 Coke and mix in jello.
Add other Coke and stir.
Add pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Let chill about 4 hours.

title: brioche
directions: Warm 1-1/2 cups water and 2 tablespoons butter to lukewarm. Mix yeast with 1 cup sugar.
Add water mixture to yeast and stir to dissolve.

title: walnut sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon color.
Add water and beat well.
Beat in sugar and gradually add flavoring.
Fold in flour, salt and nuts.
Beat whites and cream of tartar until stiff, then fold into yolk mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: green bean cream cheese casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken and cream cheese and pour over green beans.
Place onions on top.
Bake in 9x13 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers.
Cook macaroni.
Mix tomato sauce and paste with Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Start with a layer of sauce.
Add beef, then macaroni layer until all ingredients are used up.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Take out.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese has melted.

title: frosted jello salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add Seven-Up.
Let chill until partly set.
Then add drained crushed pineapple, marshmallows and sliced bananas.
Let this chill until firm.
Then add whipped cream topping.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in saucepan.
Cook to 300° (use candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay chocolate bars on top and spread while hot.
Chill thoroughly. Break into pieces.
Makes great Christmas gift.

title: crumble coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix and save 1/2 cup of mix to sprinkle over batter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy angel biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out on floured board.
Cut with small biscuit cutter and bake in hot oven at 425°.

title: chicken broccoli rice or noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute celery, onion and green pepper until tender.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix all in together and put in greased casserole dish.
Cook in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave until hot.

title: navy beans pottage
directions: Make sofrito and cook for about 3 minutes.
Add bay leaf, softened beans (either soaked overnight or cooked 30 minutes in a pressure cooker) and water.
Cook on medium heat.

title: cajun rice and sausage
directions: Brown sausage and onion in large non stick skillet over high heat, 2 minutes.

title: curried potatoes and peas
directions: *One (10 ounce) package frozen peas and carrots can be substituted for the peas and mushrooms, if preferred.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion and salt.
Mix well and form into balls.
Place in a deep baking dish.
Combine juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Pour over meatballs. Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: appetizer shrimp kabobs
directions: Peel shrimp and devein, if desired.
Set aside.
Combine lemon juice and remaining ingredients, except shrimp, in a shallow dish. Set aside.
Arrange shrimp on 6-inch bamboo skewers and place in marinade, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Remove shrimp from marinade, reserving marinade.
Place shrimp on rack of a lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil 6-inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side, basting occasionally with remaining marinade.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients (except walnuts) well.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add walnuts; stir in well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Let cool before taking cake out of pan.

title: strawberry sour cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Sort, rinse and halve berries. Place berries evenly in pastry shell. Sift flour, sugar and salt together in a medium-sized bowl. Add sour cream and stir well. Pour mixture over berries and spread evenly. Sprinkle reserved sugar over the top. Bake for 10 minutes. Reduce oven to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until crust is a gentle, golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch.
Add Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: texas style hot dog sauce
directions: Fry up hamburg; stir to a fine texture.
May season hamburger while frying with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Put in saucepan and add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 hours. You may have to add more water before it is done simmering.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add other ingredients.
Mix and spread in ungreased pan 11 x 15-inches.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until nice and brown.
Melt Hershey bar in double boiler and spread on cookies while hot.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Cut in small squares.

title: dump fruit salad
directions: Mix together, stirring well.
Strawberry instant pudding is found at Krogers.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms and green pepper in butter or oleo. Add flour and blend.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir some of the mixture into beaten egg and add to remaining hot mixture.
Continue cooking 10 minutes.
Add chicken and pimento.
Serve over hot biscuits or toast.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet or pizza pan. Completely cover bottom of pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread on cooled crust. Top with your favorite fresh vegetables.
Carrots are great for color, broccoli, green peppers, cauliflower, onions are good.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with knife into rectangular shapes.
Do not re-roll.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Frost cookies with butter frosting.
Decorate with nuts, jimmies or colored frosting. (These were always "special occasion" cookies at our house.)

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix nuts, butter or margarine, flour and brown sugar together. Bake this as a crust in a baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam, 10 to 15 minutes, at 350°; cool.

title: cinnamon pinwheels
directions: On a floured board pat the dough out into rectangular shape, about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with soft butter.
In a custard cup mix brown sugar and a few grains of cinnamon.
Spread mixture over dough.
Roll the dough keeping the roll firmly together.
Cut slices 1/2-inch thick.
Lay slices cut side down on a greased pan. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
May be iced with confectioners sugar glaze when taken from oven.

title: tart congealed asparagus salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring sugar, vinegar and 1 cup water to a boil.
Add gelatin and chill in refrigerator. Add other ingredients and pour into mold.
Will make 8 individual molds.

title: glazed chex mix
directions: Heat orange juice, brown sugar and butter just until boiling. Add almonds to Chex mix.
Pour warm glaze mix over all; stir well.
Put on cookie sheet; put in oven at 275° for 30 minutes. Stir every 5 to 10 minutes while baking in oven.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Prepare macaroni as directed and drain.
Mix hamburger, onion and macaroni together and add spaghetti sauce, pizza sauce and pepperoni.
Mix altogether and top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: nut ice box cookies
directions: Mix together oil and sugars. Add eggs, then other dry ingredients. Beat thoroughly. Add nuts last. Make into rolls, covering with waxed paper; refrigerate. Slice when ready to bake. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Dough freezes well.

title: terrie's easy pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Blend in the shortening, then add milk.
Dough will be soft and easily managed.
Roll out on floured surface.
This recipe makes a 2 crust pie.

title: roast meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat eggs with salt, pepper, thyme and nutmeg until well mixed. Stir in milk, sour cream and bread crumbs. Let stand 5 minutes so that bread crumbs can absorb moisture. Add ground round, onion, parsley and garlic. Mix lightly until blended. Turn mixture into a large baking pan. Moisten hands with water and shape mixture into an 8 x 3 x 2 1/2-inch loaf. Place bacon strips over top. Bake 45 minutes. Remove bacon strips, if desired; reserve for another purpose.

title: deviled clams
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; simmer (not brown).
Blend flour and add clams, bread, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, parsley and eggs.
Cook together.
(You can add chopped boiled eggs in clam mixture after cool.)
Scrub clam shells and pack ingredients in shells.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs; bake until brown. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Add cucumbers, onions, bell peppers, celery seed and pickling salt.
Stir well until everything has been covered.
Add: sugar, celery seed, powdered alum and white vinegar.
Stir well; put in a well covered container and put in the refrigerator.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and sugar as you would for pie crust. Beat egg yolks and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to crust mixture and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and salt.
Mix.
Combine soda and water.
Stir into oats mixture along with shortening and vanilla. Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Allow to stand 2 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 7 ingredients listed.
Put into a loaf pan. Cover with bacon strips, if desired.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple orchard cake
directions: In large bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on low for 3 minutes.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
