Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until insert comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Drizzle Lemon Glaze over cake (or glaze of your choice).

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap. Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.

title: broiled tomato halves
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water to peel (if desired).
Slice tomatoes in half.
Mix all other ingredients and spread over halved tomatoes.
Put in preheated oven on broil.
Broil 4 inches from unit for 2 to 3 minutes.
Great addition to a steak dinner! Serves 4.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown meat, adding spices.
In large casserole dish, lightly smear bottom with a couple spoons of soup. Layer ingredients in following order:
1 corn tortilla, soup, meat, onion, cheese and green chiles.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with large layer of cheese.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Cornmeal Crust.
In large skillet, brown meat with onion; pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, chilies, bouillon, chili powder and cumin; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in egg.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until hot.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add oats, salt and meat.

title: kentucky biscuits(makes 12)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in oleo or shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix quickly to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead a few times, don't over knead or the biscuits will turn hard and dry.
Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased pan.
Cut into 12 portions.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mash and mix together avocados, lemon juice and salt.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread beans or beans mixed with dip on bottom of serving container.
Next, spread avocado mixture on top of beans, then sour cream mixture on top of that.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve chilled with chips (corn or potato).
Great favorite when serving a small group or large crowd.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and mince.
Cook minced stems, onion, salt and pepper in margarine until tender.
Mix onion mixture with crushed crackers and parsley. Sprinkle inside mushroom caps with salt.
Fill and brush with melted margarine. Top with shredded Mozzarella, if desired.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 20 minutes or until tender.
Use shallow pan.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg combined with milk and 1 tablespoon flour.
Dip pieces in mixture of sesame seed, 1/2 cup flour and seasonings.
Place chicken pieces in moderately hot oil (350°). Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn chicken when browned. Reduce heat and finish cooking, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Into greased pan, dump pineapple and juice; spread.
Dump in cherry filling over pineapple.
Shake dry cake mix over the top filling evenly.
Slice oleo on mix.
Add nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook 50 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken montazuma
directions: Mix top 8 ingredients.
Layer tortillas, mix, cheese, tortillas, mix and cheese.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in punch bowl. Add 7-Up just before serving. Garnish with ice ring. Yields 40 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water.
After cooking, mash.
Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup stuffing mix.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish or spray with Pam.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown chuck, stirring to separate particles; drain.
Add mushrooms and onion, cooking a few minutes longer.
Remove from heat and blend in flour.
Add beef broth, reserved mushroom liquid, salt, pepper and ketchup.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in sour cream; heat a minute longer.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions. Serve stroganoff over noodles and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cream cheese tortillas
directions: Spread the cream cheese on tortilla.
Sprinkle garlic powder. If desired, add diced chili.
Roll up as for snack.
Or roll and cut, serving as pinwheels.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12-cup nonstick muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: barley vegetable
directions: Combine beef, water, bouillon, tomatoes, onion and basil in large pot.

title: lenten cabbage medley
directions: Squeeze sauerkraut dry.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet; brown sauerkraut
well with about 3 tablespoons brown sugar, peppercorns and bay leaf, if desired.

title: honey bun cake
directions: In approximately 9 x 12-inch pan pour 1/2 of batter into pan. Sprinkle 1/2 of dry mixture over layer of batter.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining dry mixture.
Take butter knife, go up and down pan to swirl together.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes, then 25 minutes at 300°.

title: date nut ball
directions: Melt margarine and add brown sugar and dates.
Stir in coconut. When bubbling starts, cook for 6 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and Rice Krispies. Let cool.
Shape in small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: betty's dump cake
directions: Bake in 350° oven until apples are tender - approximately 30 minutes.

title: pecan meringue dessert
directions: Make 24 hours in advance.
Beat eggs, add sugar gradually, and beat to peaks.	Fold in soda crackers, pecans and vanilla. Put in 8 by 8 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with sweetened whipped cream, and seal around edges.
cover and refrigerate over night.
Can be garnished before serving with fresh fruit (e.g. berries, kiwi, etc.), and mint leaves or berry sauce.

title: lemon breadfort morgan, colorado
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichoke hearts and stir together with all ingredients. Heat until warm.
Serve with Triscuits crackers and sesame snack sticks.

title: hot punch
directions: Put
fruit
juices
and
water in bottom of percolator. Combine allspice, salt, cloves and cinnamon in top of percolator.

title: hominy - new mexico style
directions: Mix together, place in casserole, top with Monterey Jack cheese (4 ounces, shredded).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375° for 2 1/2-quart deep Corning Ware or 1 hour at 350° for flat Pyrex casserole dish, covered.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and season hamburger.
Put refried beans in 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with hamburger.
Spread with sour cream and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with tomato wedges, olives and avocado.

title: baked apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in shallow greased pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Add water and lemon juice.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Lightly brown pieces of chicken in about a tablespoon of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and cover with water.
Let simmer until chicken is done.
Make paste with 1 tablespoon of flour and a little milk, then add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Pour over the chicken and bake at 350° until tender.

title: apple salad
directions: Cream together: margarine, eggs and powdered sugar.

title: french fry sauce
directions: Mix ketchup and mayonnaise together until smooth.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place one pie crust in bottom of pie plate.
Mix together Veg-All, soup, oleo and milk.
Add chicken.
Place second pie crust on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Crust will brown.

title: diabetic orange coconut cookies
directions: Mix liquid sweetener, orange juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter.
Add liquid and coconut. Make into roll and refrigerate.
Slice and bake at 375°.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Melt butter and add to cake mix and 2 eggs.
Mix and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and spread on 9-inch pie plate and sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients with fork.
Pour over mixture and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Defrost frozen hash browns.
Add the next seven ingredients; mix well.
Place into greased 3 quart rectangular casserole.
Mix cornflakes and melted margarine; spread on the top of potatoes.
Bake uncovered one hour at 350 degrees. Serves 15.

title: cheese roll
directions: Cream cheese together until soft and well blended.
Add garlic and nuts.
Divide mixture into 2 portions.
Roll on waxed paper with chili powder.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium pot, combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water until smooth. Stir in egg yolks.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add next three ingredients. Spoon into crust.
Beat egg whites at high speed.
Add in sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread meringue evenly over hot filling. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix milk and eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Heat oil in skillet to 360°.
Put 1/2 cup batter in funnel with finger covering hole.
Spread around, making overlapping pattern.
When brown on bottom, turn.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the raisins. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Set into a pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at approximately 350°.

title: peas and spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; add mayonnaise before serving.
All vegetables should be chilled before adding mayo.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl with fork.
Stir in butter, lemon juice, vanilla, coconut and sugar.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until knife that is inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole sprayed with Pam.
Dot with squares of buttered toast (optional).
Bake at 375° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: spinach bread
directions: Split bread lengthwise. Butter with 1/2 stick butter. Saut onions in other 1/2 of butter. Add garlic, cheese and spinach. Mix well and melt cheese. Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire and Tabasco to taste. Spread evenly on bread. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Heat at 400° until cheese is melted and bread is crispy.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Layer of beans and a layer of onions.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Pour over beans and let set.
Juice can be used again.

title: sioux fish chowder
directions: Add potatoes, onions, salt and pepper to water. Cook about 10 minutes until vegetables are soft, but not completely cooked. Add fish and cook 10 minutes. Add milk and light cream. Stir and heat 15 minutes longer. DO NOT BOIL. Serve with parsley or chives.

title: chunky chicken casserole
directions: Cook stuffing mix according to box directions.
Put stuffing into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can chicken broth; pour over stuffing.
Pick chicken into bite size pieces and place in the pan.
Mix cream of celery soup and 1/2 can chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Remove from heat; add salt, pepper and butter.
Add cracker crumbs, half the grated cheese, milk and egg.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into casserole; sprinkle remaining grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes and remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients except egg whites; mix well. In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm or chilled. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: snickers bar salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Very good.
Serves 12 to 15 easily.

title: never fail popovers
directions: Bring milk and eggs to room temperature.
Grease 6 individual custard cups or popover pans (not muffin tins).
Mix milk, flour and salt.
Place custard cups on a cookie sheet, leaving space around each cup.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Put cups in oven to warm them.
Batter should sizzle when it goes in cups.
Add eggs to batter, one at a time, not overbeating.
Pour batter into cups. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes. Do not open oven during baking time.

title: layer salad
directions: Mix lettuce, celery and onions.
Place in bottom of salad bowl. Top with sliced eggs, crumbled bacon and peas.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise.
Spread over top sealing all edges.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Mix soup and wine.
Spoon over cheese slices.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top and drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and undrained pineapple.
Stir to mix well.
Pour into an oiled 4-cup mold or 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: christmas decorations
directions: Combine all ingredients until dough is firm.
Roll and cut with any cookie cutter.
Let dry 24 hours or microwave on Low for about 15 minutes.
If going to hang, make hole in top with a straw before dough is dry.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cream eggs, sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Stir in by hand the oats, chips and nuts.
Use ice cream scoop to drop on prepared cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and salt. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour this hot syrup slowly over beaten eggs, stirring constantly. Cool. Add vanilla and pecans; pour
into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
(I don't usually let my syrup mixture cool before baking.)

title: peppermint ice
directions: Melt vanilla chips.
Add crushed candy cane.
Pour on foil lined cookie sheet to about 3/8-inch thickness.
Melt mint chocolate chips; drizzle over top.
When cool, drop foil to break into small pieces.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples and cranberries; add flour and toss to coat. Add sugar and mix well. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the corn flakes, margarine and almonds.
Put in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with corn flakes and almonds.
Refrigerate overnight and bake, uncovered,
for 1 hour in a 350° oven the next day.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor, except black olives. Add black olives by hand.
Roll on waxed paper and cover with chopped nuts.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: date and nut chewies
directions: No baking.
Bring to boil on top of stove oleo, dates and brown sugar.
Then add walnuts, coconut and Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and roll into log shape.
Will be hot to work with.
When cooled, dip into powdered sugar.

title: fried cheese ball
directions: Mix cornmeal and cheese together to make a ball. Pinch off a tablespoon of cheese mixture; dip in milk then in cracker crumbs. Fry in frying pan until lightly brown.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna according to directions; drain.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and nutmeg.
Stirring continuously, pour in milk a little at a time.
Bring to boil for 1 minute, then remove from heat and stir in parsley.

title: buckeyes(candy)
directions: Mix first three ingredients and roll in small balls.
Melt last two in double boiler.
With toothpick, dip balls in the melted chocolate, leaving a small circle at top.
Place on waxed paper.
Smooth over holes with a table knife dipped in hot water.

title: date bars (sugar free)
directions: Boil for 5 minutes, take off stove and add 1 stick of margarine.
Stir and let cool.
Add 2 teaspoons soda, 2 cups flour, 2 teaspoons cinnamon, and pinch of salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with almonds.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: penthouse chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
In skillet, brown chicken in hot shortening.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes, or until done.
Uncover last 10 to 15 minutes to crisp chicken.
Remove chicken to warm platter; pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings. Cook green pepper and onion with thyme in drippings until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Serve over chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
The moisture in the sausage and cheese will hold the mixture together.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Then beat 1 egg and 1 c. water.
Add to pie crust mixture.
Set in refrigerator until apples are ready. Line cake pan with 3/4 of dough.
Fill with apples.
Add 1 c. sugar, 2 Tbsp tapioca and cinnamon.
Roll remainder of dough and place on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Frost while warm with powdered sugar frosting.

title: pull-apart bread
directions: Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Combine the 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Grease Bundt pan. Quarter the biscuits and roll in first cinnamon sugar mixture.
Put around in pan.
Spread nuts on biscuits.
Melt oleo and add cinnamon and sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and glaze with powdered sugar, vanilla and water.

title: toasted herb rolls in loaf
directions: Let butter set until soft. Cut crusts from bottom and sides of loaf. Peel off top crust. Cut bread crosswise at 2-inch intervals, a little more than half through loaf. Then cut loaf lengthwise through middle to same depth. Blend rest of ingredients with butter. Spread on top and sides of loaf and then in cuts. Place on rack in baking pan. Bake in 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until well browned.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Place 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of mix in cup; fill with hot water.
Powdered coffee creamer can be added to give it a richer flavor.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown meat in just enough oil to keep from sticking.
Add garlic, onions, oregano and red pepper flakes.
To this add 2 cans tomato sauce.
Stir well and continue to cook.
Add chili powder and kidney beans, undrained.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons cumin if desired. Simmer mixture, uncovered, adding small amounts of water if too thick; stir occasionally.
Cook at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Add and mix next ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup each chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix marinade (soy sauces, beaten egg, honey and garlic powder).
Pour over wings and marinate overnight.

title: nacho cheese log
directions: Blend all ingredients, except parsley and poppy seed.
Chill until fairly firm.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small logs.
Roll in minced parsley and poppy seed to garnish.
Refrigerate several hours.
Remove (log or logs) for about 20 minutes before serving. Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: light bread rolls
directions: Measure warm water into a 2-cup measuring cup.
Add yeast and sugar; dissolve completely.
In a large mixing bowl, sift flour. Add shortening to flour and gradually add yeast mixture until dough is smooth and not sticky.
Let rise 1 hour.
Make rolls size desired; put in greased pan.
Let rise at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make cake according to directions. Spread peanut butter on top of both layers, then spread icing all over the cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dump in undrained pineapple and pie filling.
Spread in pan.
Pour cake mix (dry) over top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Slice butter in chunks and spread over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 mixture in a greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat to make a sauce.
Remove cake from oven after the 10 minutes and pour sauce over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour remaining batter over cake and sauce.
Bake an additional 17 to 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat, seasonings, bread crumbs, water and onion.
Form into 24 small balls.
Roll in flour; brown in hot fat.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat balls.
Cover; simmer for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Add soda to potato immediately.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Steam 2 to 3 hours in double boiler.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and cinnamon, along with nuts or raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fiesta lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, add chicken, salsa and cilantro.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange 1/2 of lasagne on top of sauce.
Combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, olives, green chilies and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture over lasagne.
Repeat, ending with sauce.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 25 to 30 minutes, turning 1/4 way every 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and uncover; sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes as cheese melts.

title: crab delight
directions: Combine all ingredients folding gently.
Do not break up crab lumps.
Form into crab cakes and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Brown under broiler.

title: langostino casserole
directions: Add the sherry to the langostinos in a bowl.

Place the bread crumbs in another bowl and pour the evaporated milk over them. Add the cheese, dry mustard and nutmeg to the bread mixture. Combine the langostinos and bread mixture and place in a flat casserole dish.
Put the remaining bread crumbs (crust pieces) and melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chilli(makes 1 nesco roaster)
directions: Brown meat with onions and celery.
Combine tomato juice, catsup, tomato soup, chili beans, salt, chilli powder, paprika, sugar and pepper.
Add browned meat, onion and celery.
Cook together so all blends.
Last, add cooked macaroni, the desired amount you wish.

title: dumplings
directions: Dice 6 to 8 stale hard rolls.
Whisk milk, eggs and dash of salt and pour over bread.
Let sit.
Chop one small onion.
Cook onion in butter and parsley.
Add to bread.
Add flour and mix well.
With wet hands, form balls.
Place balls gently in boiling salted water.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Place on rack to dry. Serve with melted butter and parsley.
(After cooking, can be frozen.
Put in buttered pan to reheat in oven or can microwave to reheat.)

title: green chile rice bake
directions: Cut the Monterey Jack cheese into 1/2-inch squares.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: turkeyburger parmigiana
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl, stir well; set aside.
Combine turkey and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl, blend well.
Divide meat into 4 equal portions, shape into 1/2-inch thick oval patty.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on wax paper, press patties in bread crumbs lightly coating each side.
Place patties in shallow baking dish coated with Pam.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes, drain.
Turn patties over, spoon tomato mixture evenly over patties. Bake an additional 8 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese, bake until cheese melts.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes 4 servings, with 280 calories per patty and 1/4 cup sauce.

title: beet pickles
directions: Recipe can be halved.
Recipe takes 5 days.
Do not refrigerate while doing this recipe.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cherry and pineapple.
Then sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly over the cherry-pineapple layer. Slice margarine and lay evenly over the dry cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over, then coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for at least 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with ice cream-cobbler style.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat well with electric mixer.
Add all other ingredients except crabmeat and 1/4 cup grated cheese. Stir crabmeat into mixture. Top with remaining 1/4 cup of grated cheese.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes, uncovered.
This can be made ahead and frozen, unbaked.
Bring to room temperature before baking.
Use king size corn chips for dipping.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Break up angel
food
cake
and spread over bottom of a very large
dish.
Mix the instant pudding according to directions on box
and
pour
over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over the pudding. Mix
strawberries and glaze together and spread over Cool Whip. (Chill.)

title: holiday hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend together in Baggie.

title: french fried pickles and peppers
directions: Heat 1-inch cooking oil in skillet to 360°.
Slightly beat egg in small bowl.
Stir in milk and pickle liquid.
Add pancake mix. Stir until smooth.
Dip pickle slices, one at a time, into batter. Fry in oil for 1 to 2 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.

title: joyce's joy
directions: Prepare 11 x 14-inch pan with nonstick spray or margarine and flour.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts into bottom of pan.
Follow directions to prepare German chocolate cake mix.
Pour cake mix over coconut and nuts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine hamburger with salt and pepper. Put meat in the bottom of lightly greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Top with layers of onions, carrots and ending with potatoes, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup with water. Pour over and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Mix milk, lemonade, pineapple and Cool Whip by hand.
Add enough marshmallows, coconut and pecans to make slightly stiff. Add some cherries and a dash of food color to make it pretty.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins until almost done. Rinse and let cool.
Peel skins and grate them into a large bowl. In saucepan, add grated cheese, milk, whipping cream, dry mustard, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat until cheese is melted. Pour mixture over potatoes and mix. Add a few butter pats and paprika.
Let cool. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cook approximately 1 hour at 300° or until hot all through.

title: cinnamon stars(zimniet sterne)
directions: Beat egg whites, adding some sugar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry. Beat egg yolks. Add sugar, milk and cinnamon; fold in whites. Add flour, baking powder and nuts. Fold in by hand.

After dough is mixed, refrigerate before rolling and cutting. Roll dough (not too thin) and cut with star cookie cutter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (do not bake too long); cookies should be soft and chewy.

title: ray's nacho supreme
directions: Brown ground beef with onions. Drain. Mix meat, soup, and rotel together until well

blended. Spray bottom of a 9x13 inch pan, cover bottom of pan heavily with nacho chips. Pour meat mixture over chips. Cover with cheese. May add more cheese if you are a cheese lover. Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and begins to brown.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup. Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and cut out. Cook in a 400° oven until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Throw everything, but vanilla, into a large saucepan.
Heat at low heat until butter melts.
Increase heat until mixture boils. Allow mixture to boil for 4 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly. (Beware, it will stick or scorch.) Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve while hot.
Makes about 1 quart of gravy.
Unused gravy can be stored in the refrigerator in a fruit jar and used indefinitely.

title: cabbage-apple salad
directions: Mix apples, cabbage and peanuts together.
In small bowl, mix peanut butter, honey and mayonnaise together.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss together.

title: scrumptious dessert
directions: Defrost Cool Whip.
Drain fruit well.
Mix pistachio pudding with Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit.
Put in dish and cool.
Will firm up in 1 hour or more.

title: reba's christmas salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup of hot water.
Add marshmallows, cream cheese and undrained pineapple.
Beat mixture until lumps disappear.
Cool.
After mixture is cool, add celery, nuts, mayonnaise and whipped topping.
Pour into shallow pan or dish; refrigerate until firm.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Refrigerate just until cooled.
Pour strawberry Jell-O on top of first mixture that has set.
Allow to cool.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: potato-peanut butter candy
directions: Boil potato with skin on until well done.
Peel and mash very fine.
Add vanilla and milk; mix well.
Add powdered sugar until like stiff dough.
Roll on wax paper sprinkled with powdered sugar to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with peanut butter; roll like jelly roll.
Make rolls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Slice about 3/8-inch thick.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Simmer together the beef, taco seasoning and water until liquid is almost gone.

title: taylor's chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and spices.
Dip chicken in margarine; then dry mixture.
Place in a single layer on baking sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: oktoberfeast
directions: Saute the chopped onion until tender.
Add 1/2 cup honey sweetened barbecue sauce to onion.
Add this sauce to contents in pita pockets.
Serve with lots of napkins!

title: hot spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a skillet, saute nuts
in butter until hot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Arrange nuts in shallow pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine and blend eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture and mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave chex mix
directions: In microwave bowl (large) melt oleo.
Add seasonings.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Microwave 6 minutes on High, stirring after each minute.
Add pretzels before last minute.
Spread on newspaper to cool.

title: quail or pheasants
directions: Grease Pyrex dish with the butter.
Pour in rice and water. Arrange birds on rice.
Mix sour cream, sherry and cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup thoroughly.
Pour over birds and cover with foil.
Cook 1 hour covered and 10 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground chuck with onions and green peppers.
Drain.
Prepare taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat.
Mix in 8 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Press crescent rolls into 10-inch glass pie plate to form crust.
Pour chuck/taco mixture into crust.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Stir together, fill and roll tortillas, and lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(You may freeze this at this point.)

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange beef
in bottom of a deep pan.
Roll each piece of chicken breast
with
a
piece
of bacon, and put on top of beef. Top
with
mushroom soup and sour cream.
I mix the two together. Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours.
Cook uncovered.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Fry until brown.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until pork chops are done.

title: crunchy squash
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion.
Add squash and water. Cover and steam for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add sugar, Accent, salt and pepper.

title: busy ladies pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers tightly almost to top of gallon glass jar. Add salt, spices and alum. Cover with white vinegar. Let set 6 weeks. Rinse cucumbers and jar to remove spices. Layer cucumbers with a layer of sugar (1 cup at a time) until 8 cups of sugar have been used. Fill to top of jar. Shake until liquid forms. Keep at room temperature. May be put in the refrigerator to chill before serving.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Leave out enough beef to roll cheese ball in.
Mix all ingredients together. Form into ball and roll in remaining dried beef. Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Cut into one-inch pieces.
Saute celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in fat until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, okra and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Divide rice into 6 bowls.
Fill with gumbo.
Serves 6.

title: turkey-walnut salad
directions: Stir together turkey and next 9 ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.
Serve over salad greens.
Serves 6.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until browned.
Drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with chili powder, salt and garlic salt.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, raw rice, water and green peppers.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts, about 3 minutes.

title: purple passion ice cream
directions: Add the above to ice cream freezer. Fill to top line with milk.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Add cut up berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Stir in a few drops food coloring.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for garnish. Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with berries.
Serves 6.

title: great grandma emma knapp's potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and fry in skillet with oil until brown and crispy.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients drop by tablespoon into 1/2 inch oil in skillet. Fry until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time. Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour in tube pan and bake for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add preserves, flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: oatmeal snowball cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients. Add vanilla and oatmeal (1 cup at a time).
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: honey chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and place chicken in it.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until well mixed.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.
